{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BNmMHXmrpqphqEoDzMeewD","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me create a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Ralph-Burning-Rewrite Directory Structure & Module Exploration\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the ralph-burning-rewrite codebase. Here's the detailed breakdown:\n\n---\n\n## 1. DIRECTORY TREE\n\n```\nralph-burning-rewrite/\n├── Cargo.toml                          # Project manifest\n├── src/\n│   ├── lib.rs                          # Public module exports\n│   ├── main.rs                         # Binary entry point (CLI dispatcher)\n│   ├── shared/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs                      # Shared module exports\n│   │   ├── domain.rs                   # Core domain types (226 lines)\n│   │   └── error.rs                    # Error types and contracts (145 lines)\n│   ├── adapters/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── fs.rs                       # Filesystem adapter (632 lines)\n│   │   └── stub_backend.rs             # Mock backend for testing\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs                      # CLI dispatcher (49 lines)\n│   │   ├── init.rs                     # `init` command\n│   │   ├── flow.rs                     # `flow` command\n│   │   ├── config.rs                   # `config` command\n│   │   ├── project.rs                  # `project` command (manage projects)\n│   │   ├── run.rs                      # `run` command (status, history, tail)\n│   │   ├── daemon.rs                   # `daemon` command (not implemented)\n│   │   ├── requirements.rs             # `requirements` command\n│   │   └── conformance.rs              # `conformance` command\n│   └── contexts/\n│       ├── mod.rs                      # Context module exports (7 domains)\n│       ├── workflow_composition/       # Stage contracts & flow definitions\n│       │   ├── mod.rs                  # Flow definitions (116 lines)\n│       │   ├── contracts.rs            # Stage contract registry\n│       │   ├── payloads.rs             # Typed payload models (130+ lines)\n│       │   └── renderers.rs            # Markdown renderers for payloads\n│       ├── project_run_record/         # Durable project & run state\n│       │   ├── mod.rs                  # Context exports\n│       │   ├── model.rs                # ProjectRecord, RunSnapshot, etc.\n│       │   ├── journal.rs              # Journal event parsing/validation\n│       │   ├── queries.rs              # Run status/history/tail queries\n│       │   └── service.rs              # Use cases + ports (100+ lines read)\n│       ├── agent_execution/            # Backend invocation & sessions\n│       │   ├── mod.rs                  # Context exports\n│       │   ├── model.rs                # InvocationRequest, tokens, etc.\n│       │   ├── service.rs              # AgentExecutionPort, BackendResolver\n│       │   └── session.rs              # SessionManager, session persistence\n│       ├── workspace_governance/       # Workspace initialization & config\n│       │   ├── mod.rs                  # Core init/config functions (135 lines)\n│       │   └── config.rs               # EffectiveConfig resolver\n│       ├── requirements_drafting/      # Stub context (1 line)\n│       ├── conformance_spec/           # Stub context (1 line)\n│       └── automation_runtime/         # Stub context (1 line)\n└── tests/\n    ├── unit.rs                         # Unit test module loader\n    ├── cli.rs                          # CLI integration tests\n    └── unit/                           # Individual unit tests\n        ├── domain_test.rs\n        ├── flow_preset_test.rs\n        ├── workspace_test.rs\n        ├── config_test.rs\n        ├── active_project_test.rs\n        ├── stage_contract_test.rs\n        ├── renderer_test.rs\n        ├── project_run_record_test.rs\n        ├── journal_test.rs\n        ├── query_test.rs\n        ├── adapter_contract_test.rs\n        ├── agent_execution_test.rs\n        └── stub_backend_test.rs\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. CARGO.TOML DEPENDENCIES\n\n**Production:**\n- `chrono` (0.4) - datetime handling with clock/serde features\n- `clap` (4.5) - CLI argument parsing with derive\n- `schemars` (0.8) - JSON schema generation\n- `serde` (1) - serialization/deserialization\n- `serde_json` (1) - JSON support\n- `thiserror` (2) - error handling macros\n- `tokio` (1) - async runtime with multi_thread, sync, time features\n- `toml` (0.8) - TOML parsing\n- `toml_edit` (0.22) - TOML document editing\n- `tracing` (0.1) - structured logging\n- `tracing-subscriber` (0.3) - logging output\n\n**Dev:**\n- `jsonschema` (0.18) - schema validation in tests\n- `tempfile` (3) - temporary file handling for tests\n\n---\n\n## 3. SHARED ERROR TYPES\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs`\n\n### `AppError` Enum (45 variants)\nAll errors implement `thiserror::Error` for automatic Display impl:\n\n**Initialization Errors:**\n- `AlreadyInitialized` - workspace already has config\n- `WorkspaceConflict` - directory exists without config\n- `UnsupportedWorkspaceVersion` - version mismatch\n\n**Configuration Errors:**\n- `InvalidStageCursorField` - cycle/attempt/round must be > 0\n- `InvalidIdentifier` - invalid project ID format\n- `InvalidFlowPreset` - unknown flow preset\n- `UnknownConfigKey` / `InvalidConfigValue`\n\n**Project Management Errors:**\n- `NoActiveProject` - no project selected\n- `ProjectNotFound` - project directory missing\n- `DuplicateProject` - project already exists\n- `ActiveRunDelete` - cannot delete active project\n- `EditorFailed` - EDITOR command failed\n\n**Data Integrity Errors:**\n- `CorruptRecord` - malformed TOML/JSON file\n- `InvalidPrompt` - unreadable prompt file\n- `JournalSequence` - non-monotonic event sequence\n\n**Backend Errors:**\n- `BackendUnavailable` - backend not accessible\n- `CapabilityMismatch` - stage not supported by backend\n- `InvocationFailed` - backend execution error (with `FailureClass`)\n- `InvocationTimeout` - backend exceeded timeout\n- `InvocationCancelled` - operation cancelled\n\n**Infrastructure:**\n- `NotYetImplemented` - placeholder for incomplete features\n- `Io` - std::io::Error\n- `TomlDeserialize`, `TomlSerialize`, `TomlEdit` - TOML errors\n- `SerdeJson` - JSON serialization errors\n\n### `ContractError` Enum (4 variants with `FailureClass` mapping)\n- `SchemaValidation` → `SchemaValidationFailure`\n- `DomainValidation` → `DomainValidationFailure`\n- `RenderError` → `DomainValidationFailure`\n- `QaReviewOutcome` → `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n---\n\n## 4. SHARED DOMAIN TYPES\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` (226 lines)\n\n### Key Enums & Structs:\n\n**FailureClass** (6 variants for retry semantics):\n- `TransportFailure`, `SchemaValidationFailure`, `DomainValidationFailure`, `Timeout`, `Cancellation`, `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n**BackendFamily** (4 variants):\n- `Claude`, `Codex`, `OpenRouter`, `Stub`\n- Methods: `as_str()`, `display_name()`, `default_model_id()`\n\n**BackendRole** (5 variants):\n- `Planner`, `Implementer`, `Reviewer`, `QaValidator`, `CompletionJudge`\n- Maps stages → roles, defines default targets & session reuse policies\n\n**FlowPreset** (4 variants):\n- `Standard` (8 stages: full flow)\n- `QuickDev` (4 stages: lightweight)\n- `DocsChange` (4 stages: docs-focused)\n- `CiImprovement` (4 stages: CI-focused)\n\n**StageId** (16 variants):\nALL: PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview, PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsPlan, DocsUpdate, DocsValidation, CiPlan, CiUpdate, CiValidation\n\n**StageCursor** (tracking position in execution):\n- `stage: StageId`\n- `cycle: u32` (work cycle counter)\n- `attempt: u32` (retry counter within stage)\n- `completion_round: u32` (completion attempt counter)\n\n**ResolvedBackendTarget**:\n- `backend: BackendSpec`\n- `model: ModelSpec`\n- Methods: `supports_stage()`, `supports_session_reuse()`\n\n**ProjectId** / **RunId**: Newtype wrappers with validation\n- Must be non-empty, no path separators, not \".\" or \"..\"\n\n**WorkspaceConfig** (persisted in `workspace.toml`):\n- `version: u32` (CURRENT = 1)\n- `created_at: DateTime<Utc>`\n- `settings: WorkspaceSettings`\n\n**WorkspaceSettings**:\n- `prompt_review: PromptReviewSettings`\n- `default_flow: Option<FlowPreset>`\n- `default_backend: Option<String>`\n- `default_model: Option<String>`\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONTEXT MODULES\n\n### A. **workflow_composition** - Stage Contracts & Flow Definitions\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs`\n\n**Types:**\n- `ValidationProfile` - validation approach per flow\n- `FlowDefinition` - preset + stages + validation rules\n\n**Functions:**\n- `built_in_flows()` - returns all 4 flow definitions\n- `flow_definition(preset)` - lookup by FlowPreset\n- `flow_definition_by_id(flow_id)` - lookup by string ID\n\n**Flow Stage Definitions:**\n```\nStandard:    [PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview]\nQuickDev:    [PlanAndImplement, Review, ApplyFixes, FinalReview]\nDocsChange:  [DocsPlan, DocsUpdate, DocsValidation, Review]\nCiImprovement: [CiPlan, CiUpdate, CiValidation, Review]\n```\n\n**contracts.rs:**\n- `ContractFamily` - enum: Planning, Execution, Validation\n- `StageContract` - binds StageId to family + schema\n- `ValidatedBundle` - typed payload + rendered Markdown artifact\n- `contract_for_stage(stage_id)` - registry lookup\n\n**payloads.rs:**\nThree typed payload families:\n\n1. **PlanningPayload** (4 fields):\n   - `problem_framing: String`\n   - `assumptions_or_open_questions: Vec<String>`\n   - `proposed_work: Vec<ProposedWorkItem>` (order, summary, details)\n   - `readiness: ReadinessAssessment` (ready, risks)\n\n2. **ExecutionPayload** (4 fields):\n   - `change_summary: String`\n   - `steps: Vec<ExecutionStep>` (order, description, status: Intended/Completed/Skipped)\n   - `validation_evidence: Vec<String>`\n   - `outstanding_risks: Vec<String>`\n\n3. **ValidationPayload** (4 fields):\n   - `outcome: ReviewOutcome` (Approved, ConditionallyApproved, RequestChanges, Rejected)\n   - `evidence: Vec<String>`\n   - `findings_or_gaps: Vec<String>`\n   - `follow_up_or_amendments: Vec<String>`\n\n**renderers.rs:**\n- `render_planning(stage_id, payload)` → deterministic Markdown\n- `render_execution(stage_id, payload)` → deterministic Markdown\n- `render_validation(stage_id, payload)` → deterministic Markdown\n- Byte-identical output for same input\n\n### B. **project_run_record** - Durable State & Run Queries\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/`\n\n**model.rs:**\n- `ProjectRecord` (immutable, persisted in `project.toml`):\n  - `id, name, flow, prompt_reference, prompt_hash, created_at, status_summary`\n- `RunSnapshot` (canonical run state, persisted in `run.json`):\n  - `active_run: Option<ActiveRun>` (run_id, stage_cursor, started_at)\n  - `status: RunStatus` (NotStarted, Running, Paused, Completed, Failed)\n  - `cycle_history: Vec<CycleHistoryEntry>`\n  - `completion_rounds: u32`\n  - `rollback_point_meta, amendment_queue`\n  - **Validates semantics:** Running/Paused requires active_run; NotStarted forbids active_run\n- `JournalEvent` (ndjson lines in `journal.ndjson`):\n  - `sequence: u64, timestamp, event_type, details`\n  - `JournalEventType`: ProjectCreated, RunStarted, StageEntered, StageCompleted, CycleAdvanced, CompletionRoundAdvanced, RunCompleted, RunFailed, RollbackCreated, AmendmentQueued\n- `PayloadRecord` (in `history/payloads/*.json`)\n- `ArtifactRecord` (in `history/artifacts/*.json`)\n- `RuntimeLogEntry` (in `runtime/logs/*.ndjson`)\n\n**service.rs:**\nPorts (interfaces):\n- `ProjectStorePort` - CRUD project records, atomic creation, staged delete\n- `JournalStorePort` - read/append journal events\n- `ArtifactStorePort` - list payloads and artifacts\n- `RuntimeLogStorePort` - read runtime logs\n- `RunSnapshotPort` - read run snapshot\n- `ActiveProjectPort` - manage active project pointer\n\nUse Cases:\n- `create_project(input)` - CreateProjectInput struct\n- `list_projects()`, `show_project(id)`\n- `delete_project(id)` - with 2-phase delete (stage → commit)\n- `run_status(store, base_dir, project_id)` - query current status\n- `run_history(journal, artifacts, base_dir, project_id)` - durable history\n- `run_tail(journal, artifacts, logs, base_dir, project_id, include_logs)` - recent state\n\n**journal.rs:**\n- `validate_sequence(last_seq, event)` - ensures monotonic ordering\n- `serialize_event(event)` → NDJSON line\n- `deserialize_event(line)` → JournalEvent\n- `parse_journal(contents)` - full file parsing + integrity check\n\n### C. **agent_execution** - Backend Invocation & Session Management\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/`\n\n**model.rs:**\n- `CancellationToken` - Arc<AtomicBool> + Notify for async cancellation\n- `InvocationPayload` - `prompt: String, context: Value`\n- `InvocationRequest` - complete invocation spec:\n  - `invocation_id, project_root, stage_contract, role, resolved_target`\n  - `payload, timeout, cancellation_token, session_policy, prior_session, attempt_number`\n- `InvocationEnvelope` - result wrapper\n- `InvocationMetadata` - metadata about invocation\n- `RawOutputReference` - reference to persisted backend output\n- `TokenCounts` - token usage tracking\n- `CapabilityCheck` - capability validation result\n\n**service.rs:**\n- `AgentExecutionPort` trait:\n  - `check_capability()` - verify stage support\n  - `check_availability()` - verify backend running\n  - `invoke()` → InvocationEnvelope\n- `AgentExecutionService<B, O, S>` - generic over Backend, RawOutputStore, SessionStore\n- `BackendSelectionConfig` - backend family + model_id overrides\n- `BackendResolver` - multi-level resolution:\n  - Role defaults → Workspace config → Project config → Explicit override\n  - `resolve()` method with cascading precedence\n\n**session.rs:**\n- `SessionMetadata` - persisted session info:\n  - `role, backend_family, model_id, session_id, created_at, last_used_at, invocation_count`\n- `PersistedSessions` - collection of SessionMetadata\n- `SessionStorePort` trait:\n  - `load_sessions(project_root)` → PersistedSessions\n  - `save_sessions(project_root, sessions)`\n- `SessionManager<S>` - reusable session lookup:\n  - `load_reusable_session()` - respects SessionPolicy\n  - `record_session()` - updates session metadata\n\n### D. **workspace_governance** - Initialization & Config\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/`\n\n**mod.rs:**\n- Constants:\n  - `WORKSPACE_DIR = \".ralph-burning\"`\n  - `WORKSPACE_CONFIG_FILE = \"workspace.toml\"`\n  - `ACTIVE_PROJECT_FILE = \"active-project\"`\n  - `PROJECTS_DIR = \"projects\"`\n  - `PROJECT_CONFIG_FILE = \"project.toml\"`\n  - `REQUIRED_WORKSPACE_DIRECTORIES = [\"projects\", \"requirements\", \"daemon/tasks\", \"daemon/leases\"]`\n\n- Functions:\n  - `initialize_workspace(base_dir, created_at)` → WorkspaceInitialization\n  - `load_workspace_config(base_dir)` → WorkspaceConfig\n  - `ensure_supported_workspace_version(config)`\n  - `resolve_active_project(base_dir)` → ProjectId\n  - `set_active_project(base_dir, project_id)`\n\n**config.rs:**\n- `ConfigValueSource` - Default vs WorkspaceToml\n- `ConfigValue` - Bool, FlowPreset, String(Option<String>)\n- `ConfigEntry` - key, value, source tuple\n- `EffectiveConfig` - cascade resolver:\n  - Loads workspace.toml\n  - Resolves: prompt_review_enabled, default_flow, default_backend, default_model\n  - `DEFAULT_PROMPT_REVIEW_ENABLED = true`\n  - `DEFAULT_FLOW_PRESET = FlowPreset::Standard`\n\n### E. **requirements_drafting, conformance_spec, automation_runtime** - Stubs\nSingle constants defining context names (not yet implemented).\n\n---\n\n## 6. ADAPTERS/FS.RS - Filesystem Backend Implementation\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` (632 lines)\n\n### FileSystem Utility Struct\n- `create_workspace(workspace_root, config_str, required_dirs)` - init\n- `read_to_string(path)` - simple file read\n- `write_atomic(path, contents)` - atomic write via temp file + rename\n- `render_workspace_config(config)` → TOML pretty-printed\n- `read_active_project(workspace_root)` → Option<String>\n- `write_active_project(workspace_root, project_id)`\n- `open_editor(path)` - launch EDITOR/VISUAL\n- `prompt_hash(contents)` - DefaultHasher for integrity\n\n### Port Implementations\n\n**FsProjectStore** implements `ProjectStorePort`:\n- Tracks `.{id}.pending-delete` directories for transactional deletes\n- `project_exists()`, `read_project_record()`, `list_project_ids()`\n- `stage_delete()` → atomic rename to pending-delete\n- `commit_delete()` → permanent removal\n- `rollback_delete()` → restore from pending-delete\n- `create_project_atomic()` → staging + atomic rename (creates project.toml, prompt.md, run.json, journal.ndjson, sessions.json)\n\n**FsJournalStore** implements `JournalStorePort`:\n- Reads full `journal.ndjson` via `journal::parse_journal()`\n- Appends new events as lines\n\n**FsArtifactStore** implements `ArtifactStorePort`:\n- Lists JSON files from `history/payloads/`\n- Lists JSON files from `history/artifacts/`\n- Sorts by creation time\n\n**FsRuntimeLogStore** implements `RuntimeLogStorePort`:\n- Reads newest `.ndjson` file from `runtime/logs/`\n- Returns parsed RuntimeLogEntry objects\n\n**FsRunSnapshotStore** implements `RunSnapshotPort`:\n- Reads and validates `run.json` semantics\n- Rejects inconsistent status/active_run combinations\n\n**FsActiveProjectStore** implements `ActiveProjectPort`:\n- Read/clear/write active project pointer\n\n**FsRawOutputStore** implements `RawOutputPort`:\n- Persists raw output to `runtime/backend/{invocation_id}.raw`\n\n**FsSessionStore** implements `SessionStorePort`:\n- Load/save `sessions.json` as PersistedSessions\n\n---\n\n## 7. CLI STRUCTURE\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/mod.rs`\n\n```\nralph-burning (binary)\n├── init                           # Initialize workspace\n├── flow                          # Flow management\n│   ├── list                      # List all flows\n│   └── show <flow_id>           # Show flow details\n├── config                        # Config management\n├── project                       # Project management\n│   ├── create --id --name --prompt --flow\n│   ├── select <id>\n│   ├── list\n│   ├── show [id]\n│   └── delete <id>\n├── run                          # Run lifecycle\n│   ├── start\n│   ├── resume\n│   ├── status\n│   ├── history\n│   ├── tail [--logs]\n│   └── rollback --to <id> [--hard]\n├── requirements                 # Requirements management\n├── daemon                        # Daemon operations\n└── conformance                   # Conformance testing\n```\n\n### run.rs (213 lines) - Implemented Commands\n\n- `Status` - shows project, status, stage, cycle, completion_round, summary\n- `History` - shows journal events + payloads + artifacts\n- `Tail [--logs]` - shows durable history + optional runtime logs\n- `Start`, `Resume`, `Rollback` - NotYetImplemented placeholders\n\n**Functions:**\n- `build_agent_execution_service()` - factory for AgentExecutionService<StubBackendAdapter, FsRawOutputStore, FsSessionStore>\n- `handle_status()` - calls workspace_governance + FsProjectStore + service::run_status()\n- `handle_history()` - calls FsJournalStore + FsArtifactStore\n- `handle_tail()` - calls FsJournalStore + FsArtifactStore + FsRuntimeLogStore\n\n### project.rs (80+ lines)\n\n- `Create` - validates project ID, flow, prompt file; calls service::create_project()\n- `Select` - sets active project\n- `List` - lists all projects\n- `Show [id]` - shows single project details\n- `Delete` - marks project for deletion\n\n### Other CLI Modules\n- **init.rs** - workspace initialization\n- **flow.rs** - flow listing and details\n- **config.rs** - config get/set\n- **daemon.rs**, **requirements.rs**, **conformance.rs** - stubs\n\n---\n\n## 8. TEST STRUCTURE\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/`\n\n### Integration Test: cli.rs\n- Uses tempfile for temporary workspace\n- Fixtures:\n  - `initialize_workspace_fixture()` - runs `ralph-burning init`\n  - `create_project_fixture()` - manually creates canonical project files\n- Test helpers for spawning CLI processes\n\n### Unit Tests (13 files in tests/unit/):\n\n| Test File | Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|\n| domain_test.rs | Domain types validation |\n| flow_preset_test.rs | Flow definition logic |\n| workspace_test.rs | Workspace initialization |\n| config_test.rs | Config resolution cascade |\n| active_project_test.rs | Active project selection |\n| stage_contract_test.rs | Contract registry (8 contracts validated) |\n| renderer_test.rs | Payload rendering (deterministic output) |\n| project_run_record_test.rs | ProjectRecord/RunSnapshot (23k lines) |\n| journal_test.rs | Journal parsing/validation |\n| query_test.rs | run_status/run_history/run_tail |\n| adapter_contract_test.rs | Port implementations (24k lines) |\n| agent_execution_test.rs | BackendResolver, session mgmt (18k lines) |\n| stub_backend_test.rs | StubBackendAdapter behavior |\n\n---\n\n## 9. KEY DESIGN PATTERNS\n\n1. **Ports & Adapters (Hexagonal Architecture)**\n   - Services define trait ports (ProjectStorePort, JournalStorePort, etc.)\n   - Filesystem adapter implements ports\n   - StubBackendAdapter for testing\n\n2. **Atomic Transactional Operations**\n   - Staging directory for project creation\n   - Pending-delete marker for safe project deletion\n   - Write-then-rename for atomicity\n\n3. **Canonical State Over Inference**\n   - RunSnapshot is single source of truth\n   - Journal is durable event log\n   - Payloads/artifacts are historical reference only\n\n4. **Deterministic Rendering**\n   - Payloads must render to identical Markdown for same input\n   - Prevents \"different output, same logic\" bugs\n\n5. **Cascade Configuration Resolution**\n   - Role defaults → Workspace config → Project config → Explicit override\n   - EffectiveConfig resolver handles precedence\n\n6. **Session Reuse Policy**\n   - Not all roles/backends support reuse\n   - SessionPolicy enum controls behavior\n   - SessionManager respects capabilities\n\n---\n\n## 10. PROJECT FILESYSTEM LAYOUT\n\nWhen a project is created, the following structure is initialized:\n\n```\n.ralph-burning/projects/{project_id}/\n├── project.toml                     # Immutable metadata\n├── prompt.md                        # User requirements (immutable reference)\n├── run.json                         # Canonical run state (mutable)\n├── journal.ndjson                   # Durable event log (append-only)\n├── sessions.json                    # Persisted session metadata\n├── history/\n│   ├── payloads/*.json             # Structured stage outputs\n│   └── artifacts/*.json            # Rendered Markdown artifacts\n├── runtime/\n│   ├── backend/*.raw               # Raw backend responses\n│   ├── logs/*.ndjson               # Runtime execution logs\n│   └── temp/                       # Temporary files\n├── amendments/                      # Amendment history\n└── rollback/                        # Rollback point storage\n```\n\n---\n\n## 11. SUMMARY\n\nThe ralph-burning-rewrite is a **well-architected, modular Rust CLI** with:\n\n- **36 Rust source files** across 7 context modules (workflow_composition, project_run_record, agent_execution, workspace_governance, + 3 stubs)\n- **Hexagonal architecture** with clear port definitions and filesystem adapters\n- **Durable state management** using canonical TOML/JSON/NDJSON files\n- **Transactional safety** for project creation/deletion\n- **Deterministic rendering** for stage payloads\n- **16 stage types** across 4 flow presets\n- **3 payload families** (Planning, Execution, Validation) with strict schemas\n- **Comprehensive test coverage** (13 unit test files + CLI integration tests)\n- **StubBackendAdapter** for isolated testing without external dependencies\n\nAll paths listed above are absolute paths from `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/` base directory."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad54ffdcc8b3bd366 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 74835\ntool_uses: 44\nduration_ms: 93179</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b9859e69-5579-4e82-ac66-49d19cc80e05","uuid":"46fb357c-3f70-4007-82ca-e0446c795256","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the ralph-burning-rewrite directory structure. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory tree (src/, tests/, etc.)\n2. All existing module files and their exports\n3. The Cargo.toml dependencies\n4. The current CLI structure (especially run.rs if it exists)\n5. All existing context modules (workflow_composition, project_run_record, agent_execution, workspace_governance)\n6. The shared error types\n7. The adapters/fs.rs file\n8. Test structure\n\nGive me detailed file listings and key content summaries for each area.","agentId":"ad54ffdcc8b3bd366","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have enough information. Let me create a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Ralph-Burning-Rewrite Directory Structure & Module Exploration\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the ralph-burning-rewrite codebase. Here's the detailed breakdown:\n\n---\n\n## 1. DIRECTORY TREE\n\n```\nralph-burning-rewrite/\n├── Cargo.toml                          # Project manifest\n├── src/\n│   ├── lib.rs                          # Public module exports\n│   ├── main.rs                         # Binary entry point (CLI dispatcher)\n│   ├── shared/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs                      # Shared module exports\n│   │   ├── domain.rs                   # Core domain types (226 lines)\n│   │   └── error.rs                    # Error types and contracts (145 lines)\n│   ├── adapters/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── fs.rs                       # Filesystem adapter (632 lines)\n│   │   └── stub_backend.rs             # Mock backend for testing\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── mod.rs                      # CLI dispatcher (49 lines)\n│   │   ├── init.rs                     # `init` command\n│   │   ├── flow.rs                     # `flow` command\n│   │   ├── config.rs                   # `config` command\n│   │   ├── project.rs                  # `project` command (manage projects)\n│   │   ├── run.rs                      # `run` command (status, history, tail)\n│   │   ├── daemon.rs                   # `daemon` command (not implemented)\n│   │   ├── requirements.rs             # `requirements` command\n│   │   └── conformance.rs              # `conformance` command\n│   └── contexts/\n│       ├── mod.rs                      # Context module exports (7 domains)\n│       ├── workflow_composition/       # Stage contracts & flow definitions\n│       │   ├── mod.rs                  # Flow definitions (116 lines)\n│       │   ├── contracts.rs            # Stage contract registry\n│       │   ├── payloads.rs             # Typed payload models (130+ lines)\n│       │   └── renderers.rs            # Markdown renderers for payloads\n│       ├── project_run_record/         # Durable project & run state\n│       │   ├── mod.rs                  # Context exports\n│       │   ├── model.rs                # ProjectRecord, RunSnapshot, etc.\n│       │   ├── journal.rs              # Journal event parsing/validation\n│       │   ├── queries.rs              # Run status/history/tail queries\n│       │   └── service.rs              # Use cases + ports (100+ lines read)\n│       ├── agent_execution/            # Backend invocation & sessions\n│       │   ├── mod.rs                  # Context exports\n│       │   ├── model.rs                # InvocationRequest, tokens, etc.\n│       │   ├── service.rs              # AgentExecutionPort, BackendResolver\n│       │   └── session.rs              # SessionManager, session persistence\n│       ├── workspace_governance/       # Workspace initialization & config\n│       │   ├── mod.rs                  # Core init/config functions (135 lines)\n│       │   └── config.rs               # EffectiveConfig resolver\n│       ├── requirements_drafting/      # Stub context (1 line)\n│       ├── conformance_spec/           # Stub context (1 line)\n│       └── automation_runtime/         # Stub context (1 line)\n└── tests/\n    ├── unit.rs                         # Unit test module loader\n    ├── cli.rs                          # CLI integration tests\n    └── unit/                           # Individual unit tests\n        ├── domain_test.rs\n        ├── flow_preset_test.rs\n        ├── workspace_test.rs\n        ├── config_test.rs\n        ├── active_project_test.rs\n        ├── stage_contract_test.rs\n        ├── renderer_test.rs\n        ├── project_run_record_test.rs\n        ├── journal_test.rs\n        ├── query_test.rs\n        ├── adapter_contract_test.rs\n        ├── agent_execution_test.rs\n        └── stub_backend_test.rs\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. CARGO.TOML DEPENDENCIES\n\n**Production:**\n- `chrono` (0.4) - datetime handling with clock/serde features\n- `clap` (4.5) - CLI argument parsing with derive\n- `schemars` (0.8) - JSON schema generation\n- `serde` (1) - serialization/deserialization\n- `serde_json` (1) - JSON support\n- `thiserror` (2) - error handling macros\n- `tokio` (1) - async runtime with multi_thread, sync, time features\n- `toml` (0.8) - TOML parsing\n- `toml_edit` (0.22) - TOML document editing\n- `tracing` (0.1) - structured logging\n- `tracing-subscriber` (0.3) - logging output\n\n**Dev:**\n- `jsonschema` (0.18) - schema validation in tests\n- `tempfile` (3) - temporary file handling for tests\n\n---\n\n## 3. SHARED ERROR TYPES\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs`\n\n### `AppError` Enum (45 variants)\nAll errors implement `thiserror::Error` for automatic Display impl:\n\n**Initialization Errors:**\n- `AlreadyInitialized` - workspace already has config\n- `WorkspaceConflict` - directory exists without config\n- `UnsupportedWorkspaceVersion` - version mismatch\n\n**Configuration Errors:**\n- `InvalidStageCursorField` - cycle/attempt/round must be > 0\n- `InvalidIdentifier` - invalid project ID format\n- `InvalidFlowPreset` - unknown flow preset\n- `UnknownConfigKey` / `InvalidConfigValue`\n\n**Project Management Errors:**\n- `NoActiveProject` - no project selected\n- `ProjectNotFound` - project directory missing\n- `DuplicateProject` - project already exists\n- `ActiveRunDelete` - cannot delete active project\n- `EditorFailed` - EDITOR command failed\n\n**Data Integrity Errors:**\n- `CorruptRecord` - malformed TOML/JSON file\n- `InvalidPrompt` - unreadable prompt file\n- `JournalSequence` - non-monotonic event sequence\n\n**Backend Errors:**\n- `BackendUnavailable` - backend not accessible\n- `CapabilityMismatch` - stage not supported by backend\n- `InvocationFailed` - backend execution error (with `FailureClass`)\n- `InvocationTimeout` - backend exceeded timeout\n- `InvocationCancelled` - operation cancelled\n\n**Infrastructure:**\n- `NotYetImplemented` - placeholder for incomplete features\n- `Io` - std::io::Error\n- `TomlDeserialize`, `TomlSerialize`, `TomlEdit` - TOML errors\n- `SerdeJson` - JSON serialization errors\n\n### `ContractError` Enum (4 variants with `FailureClass` mapping)\n- `SchemaValidation` → `SchemaValidationFailure`\n- `DomainValidation` → `DomainValidationFailure`\n- `RenderError` → `DomainValidationFailure`\n- `QaReviewOutcome` → `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n---\n\n## 4. SHARED DOMAIN TYPES\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` (226 lines)\n\n### Key Enums & Structs:\n\n**FailureClass** (6 variants for retry semantics):\n- `TransportFailure`, `SchemaValidationFailure`, `DomainValidationFailure`, `Timeout`, `Cancellation`, `QaReviewOutcomeFailure`\n\n**BackendFamily** (4 variants):\n- `Claude`, `Codex`, `OpenRouter`, `Stub`\n- Methods: `as_str()`, `display_name()`, `default_model_id()`\n\n**BackendRole** (5 variants):\n- `Planner`, `Implementer`, `Reviewer`, `QaValidator`, `CompletionJudge`\n- Maps stages → roles, defines default targets & session reuse policies\n\n**FlowPreset** (4 variants):\n- `Standard` (8 stages: full flow)\n- `QuickDev` (4 stages: lightweight)\n- `DocsChange` (4 stages: docs-focused)\n- `CiImprovement` (4 stages: CI-focused)\n\n**StageId** (16 variants):\nALL: PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview, PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsPlan, DocsUpdate, DocsValidation, CiPlan, CiUpdate, CiValidation\n\n**StageCursor** (tracking position in execution):\n- `stage: StageId`\n- `cycle: u32` (work cycle counter)\n- `attempt: u32` (retry counter within stage)\n- `completion_round: u32` (completion attempt counter)\n\n**ResolvedBackendTarget**:\n- `backend: BackendSpec`\n- `model: ModelSpec`\n- Methods: `supports_stage()`, `supports_session_reuse()`\n\n**ProjectId** / **RunId**: Newtype wrappers with validation\n- Must be non-empty, no path separators, not \".\" or \"..\"\n\n**WorkspaceConfig** (persisted in `workspace.toml`):\n- `version: u32` (CURRENT = 1)\n- `created_at: DateTime<Utc>`\n- `settings: WorkspaceSettings`\n\n**WorkspaceSettings**:\n- `prompt_review: PromptReviewSettings`\n- `default_flow: Option<FlowPreset>`\n- `default_backend: Option<String>`\n- `default_model: Option<String>`\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONTEXT MODULES\n\n### A. **workflow_composition** - Stage Contracts & Flow Definitions\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs`\n\n**Types:**\n- `ValidationProfile` - validation approach per flow\n- `FlowDefinition` - preset + stages + validation rules\n\n**Functions:**\n- `built_in_flows()` - returns all 4 flow definitions\n- `flow_definition(preset)` - lookup by FlowPreset\n- `flow_definition_by_id(flow_id)` - lookup by string ID\n\n**Flow Stage Definitions:**\n```\nStandard:    [PromptReview, Planning, Implementation, Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview]\nQuickDev:    [PlanAndImplement, Review, ApplyFixes, FinalReview]\nDocsChange:  [DocsPlan, DocsUpdate, DocsValidation, Review]\nCiImprovement: [CiPlan, CiUpdate, CiValidation, Review]\n```\n\n**contracts.rs:**\n- `ContractFamily` - enum: Planning, Execution, Validation\n- `StageContract` - binds StageId to family + schema\n- `ValidatedBundle` - typed payload + rendered Markdown artifact\n- `contract_for_stage(stage_id)` - registry lookup\n\n**payloads.rs:**\nThree typed payload families:\n\n1. **PlanningPayload** (4 fields):\n   - `problem_framing: String`\n   - `assumptions_or_open_questions: Vec<String>`\n   - `proposed_work: Vec<ProposedWorkItem>` (order, summary, details)\n   - `readiness: ReadinessAssessment` (ready, risks)\n\n2. **ExecutionPayload** (4 fields):\n   - `change_summary: String`\n   - `steps: Vec<ExecutionStep>` (order, description, status: Intended/Completed/Skipped)\n   - `validation_evidence: Vec<String>`\n   - `outstanding_risks: Vec<String>`\n\n3. **ValidationPayload** (4 fields):\n   - `outcome: ReviewOutcome` (Approved, ConditionallyApproved, RequestChanges, Rejected)\n   - `evidence: Vec<String>`\n   - `findings_or_gaps: Vec<String>`\n   - `follow_up_or_amendments: Vec<String>`\n\n**renderers.rs:**\n- `render_planning(stage_id, payload)` → deterministic Markdown\n- `render_execution(stage_id, payload)` → deterministic Markdown\n- `render_validation(stage_id, payload)` → deterministic Markdown\n- Byte-identical output for same input\n\n### B. **project_run_record** - Durable State & Run Queries\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/`\n\n**model.rs:**\n- `ProjectRecord` (immutable, persisted in `project.toml`):\n  - `id, name, flow, prompt_reference, prompt_hash, created_at, status_summary`\n- `RunSnapshot` (canonical run state, persisted in `run.json`):\n  - `active_run: Option<ActiveRun>` (run_id, stage_cursor, started_at)\n  - `status: RunStatus` (NotStarted, Running, Paused, Completed, Failed)\n  - `cycle_history: Vec<CycleHistoryEntry>`\n  - `completion_rounds: u32`\n  - `rollback_point_meta, amendment_queue`\n  - **Validates semantics:** Running/Paused requires active_run; NotStarted forbids active_run\n- `JournalEvent` (ndjson lines in `journal.ndjson`):\n  - `sequence: u64, timestamp, event_type, details`\n  - `JournalEventType`: ProjectCreated, RunStarted, StageEntered, StageCompleted, CycleAdvanced, CompletionRoundAdvanced, RunCompleted, RunFailed, RollbackCreated, AmendmentQueued\n- `PayloadRecord` (in `history/payloads/*.json`)\n- `ArtifactRecord` (in `history/artifacts/*.json`)\n- `RuntimeLogEntry` (in `runtime/logs/*.ndjson`)\n\n**service.rs:**\nPorts (interfaces):\n- `ProjectStorePort` - CRUD project records, atomic creation, staged delete\n- `JournalStorePort` - read/append journal events\n- `ArtifactStorePort` - list payloads and artifacts\n- `RuntimeLogStorePort` - read runtime logs\n- `RunSnapshotPort` - read run snapshot\n- `ActiveProjectPort` - manage active project pointer\n\nUse Cases:\n- `create_project(input)` - CreateProjectInput struct\n- `list_projects()`, `show_project(id)`\n- `delete_project(id)` - with 2-phase delete (stage → commit)\n- `run_status(store, base_dir, project_id)` - query current status\n- `run_history(journal, artifacts, base_dir, project_id)` - durable history\n- `run_tail(journal, artifacts, logs, base_dir, project_id, include_logs)` - recent state\n\n**journal.rs:**\n- `validate_sequence(last_seq, event)` - ensures monotonic ordering\n- `serialize_event(event)` → NDJSON line\n- `deserialize_event(line)` → JournalEvent\n- `parse_journal(contents)` - full file parsing + integrity check\n\n### C. **agent_execution** - Backend Invocation & Session Management\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/`\n\n**model.rs:**\n- `CancellationToken` - Arc<AtomicBool> + Notify for async cancellation\n- `InvocationPayload` - `prompt: String, context: Value`\n- `InvocationRequest` - complete invocation spec:\n  - `invocation_id, project_root, stage_contract, role, resolved_target`\n  - `payload, timeout, cancellation_token, session_policy, prior_session, attempt_number`\n- `InvocationEnvelope` - result wrapper\n- `InvocationMetadata` - metadata about invocation\n- `RawOutputReference` - reference to persisted backend output\n- `TokenCounts` - token usage tracking\n- `CapabilityCheck` - capability validation result\n\n**service.rs:**\n- `AgentExecutionPort` trait:\n  - `check_capability()` - verify stage support\n  - `check_availability()` - verify backend running\n  - `invoke()` → InvocationEnvelope\n- `AgentExecutionService<B, O, S>` - generic over Backend, RawOutputStore, SessionStore\n- `BackendSelectionConfig` - backend family + model_id overrides\n- `BackendResolver` - multi-level resolution:\n  - Role defaults → Workspace config → Project config → Explicit override\n  - `resolve()` method with cascading precedence\n\n**session.rs:**\n- `SessionMetadata` - persisted session info:\n  - `role, backend_family, model_id, session_id, created_at, last_used_at, invocation_count`\n- `PersistedSessions` - collection of SessionMetadata\n- `SessionStorePort` trait:\n  - `load_sessions(project_root)` → PersistedSessions\n  - `save_sessions(project_root, sessions)`\n- `SessionManager<S>` - reusable session lookup:\n  - `load_reusable_session()` - respects SessionPolicy\n  - `record_session()` - updates session metadata\n\n### D. **workspace_governance** - Initialization & Config\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workspace_governance/`\n\n**mod.rs:**\n- Constants:\n  - `WORKSPACE_DIR = \".ralph-burning\"`\n  - `WORKSPACE_CONFIG_FILE = \"workspace.toml\"`\n  - `ACTIVE_PROJECT_FILE = \"active-project\"`\n  - `PROJECTS_DIR = \"projects\"`\n  - `PROJECT_CONFIG_FILE = \"project.toml\"`\n  - `REQUIRED_WORKSPACE_DIRECTORIES = [\"projects\", \"requirements\", \"daemon/tasks\", \"daemon/leases\"]`\n\n- Functions:\n  - `initialize_workspace(base_dir, created_at)` → WorkspaceInitialization\n  - `load_workspace_config(base_dir)` → WorkspaceConfig\n  - `ensure_supported_workspace_version(config)`\n  - `resolve_active_project(base_dir)` → ProjectId\n  - `set_active_project(base_dir, project_id)`\n\n**config.rs:**\n- `ConfigValueSource` - Default vs WorkspaceToml\n- `ConfigValue` - Bool, FlowPreset, String(Option<String>)\n- `ConfigEntry` - key, value, source tuple\n- `EffectiveConfig` - cascade resolver:\n  - Loads workspace.toml\n  - Resolves: prompt_review_enabled, default_flow, default_backend, default_model\n  - `DEFAULT_PROMPT_REVIEW_ENABLED = true`\n  - `DEFAULT_FLOW_PRESET = FlowPreset::Standard`\n\n### E. **requirements_drafting, conformance_spec, automation_runtime** - Stubs\nSingle constants defining context names (not yet implemented).\n\n---\n\n## 6. ADAPTERS/FS.RS - Filesystem Backend Implementation\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` (632 lines)\n\n### FileSystem Utility Struct\n- `create_workspace(workspace_root, config_str, required_dirs)` - init\n- `read_to_string(path)` - simple file read\n- `write_atomic(path, contents)` - atomic write via temp file + rename\n- `render_workspace_config(config)` → TOML pretty-printed\n- `read_active_project(workspace_root)` → Option<String>\n- `write_active_project(workspace_root, project_id)`\n- `open_editor(path)` - launch EDITOR/VISUAL\n- `prompt_hash(contents)` - DefaultHasher for integrity\n\n### Port Implementations\n\n**FsProjectStore** implements `ProjectStorePort`:\n- Tracks `.{id}.pending-delete` directories for transactional deletes\n- `project_exists()`, `read_project_record()`, `list_project_ids()`\n- `stage_delete()` → atomic rename to pending-delete\n- `commit_delete()` → permanent removal\n- `rollback_delete()` → restore from pending-delete\n- `create_project_atomic()` → staging + atomic rename (creates project.toml, prompt.md, run.json, journal.ndjson, sessions.json)\n\n**FsJournalStore** implements `JournalStorePort`:\n- Reads full `journal.ndjson` via `journal::parse_journal()`\n- Appends new events as lines\n\n**FsArtifactStore** implements `ArtifactStorePort`:\n- Lists JSON files from `history/payloads/`\n- Lists JSON files from `history/artifacts/`\n- Sorts by creation time\n\n**FsRuntimeLogStore** implements `RuntimeLogStorePort`:\n- Reads newest `.ndjson` file from `runtime/logs/`\n- Returns parsed RuntimeLogEntry objects\n\n**FsRunSnapshotStore** implements `RunSnapshotPort`:\n- Reads and validates `run.json` semantics\n- Rejects inconsistent status/active_run combinations\n\n**FsActiveProjectStore** implements `ActiveProjectPort`:\n- Read/clear/write active project pointer\n\n**FsRawOutputStore** implements `RawOutputPort`:\n- Persists raw output to `runtime/backend/{invocation_id}.raw`\n\n**FsSessionStore** implements `SessionStorePort`:\n- Load/save `sessions.json` as PersistedSessions\n\n---\n\n## 7. CLI STRUCTURE\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/mod.rs`\n\n```\nralph-burning (binary)\n├── init                           # Initialize workspace\n├── flow                          # Flow management\n│   ├── list                      # List all flows\n│   └── show <flow_id>           # Show flow details\n├── config                        # Config management\n├── project                       # Project management\n│   ├── create --id --name --prompt --flow\n│   ├── select <id>\n│   ├── list\n│   ├── show [id]\n│   └── delete <id>\n├── run                          # Run lifecycle\n│   ├── start\n│   ├── resume\n│   ├── status\n│   ├── history\n│   ├── tail [--logs]\n│   └── rollback --to <id> [--hard]\n├── requirements                 # Requirements management\n├── daemon                        # Daemon operations\n└── conformance                   # Conformance testing\n```\n\n### run.rs (213 lines) - Implemented Commands\n\n- `Status` - shows project, status, stage, cycle, completion_round, summary\n- `History` - shows journal events + payloads + artifacts\n- `Tail [--logs]` - shows durable history + optional runtime logs\n- `Start`, `Resume`, `Rollback` - NotYetImplemented placeholders\n\n**Functions:**\n- `build_agent_execution_service()` - factory for AgentExecutionService<StubBackendAdapter, FsRawOutputStore, FsSessionStore>\n- `handle_status()` - calls workspace_governance + FsProjectStore + service::run_status()\n- `handle_history()` - calls FsJournalStore + FsArtifactStore\n- `handle_tail()` - calls FsJournalStore + FsArtifactStore + FsRuntimeLogStore\n\n### project.rs (80+ lines)\n\n- `Create` - validates project ID, flow, prompt file; calls service::create_project()\n- `Select` - sets active project\n- `List` - lists all projects\n- `Show [id]` - shows single project details\n- `Delete` - marks project for deletion\n\n### Other CLI Modules\n- **init.rs** - workspace initialization\n- **flow.rs** - flow listing and details\n- **config.rs** - config get/set\n- **daemon.rs**, **requirements.rs**, **conformance.rs** - stubs\n\n---\n\n## 8. TEST STRUCTURE\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/`\n\n### Integration Test: cli.rs\n- Uses tempfile for temporary workspace\n- Fixtures:\n  - `initialize_workspace_fixture()` - runs `ralph-burning init`\n  - `create_project_fixture()` - manually creates canonical project files\n- Test helpers for spawning CLI processes\n\n### Unit Tests (13 files in tests/unit/):\n\n| Test File | Coverage |\n|-----------|----------|\n| domain_test.rs | Domain types validation |\n| flow_preset_test.rs | Flow definition logic |\n| workspace_test.rs | Workspace initialization |\n| config_test.rs | Config resolution cascade |\n| active_project_test.rs | Active project selection |\n| stage_contract_test.rs | Contract registry (8 contracts validated) |\n| renderer_test.rs | Payload rendering (deterministic output) |\n| project_run_record_test.rs | ProjectRecord/RunSnapshot (23k lines) |\n| journal_test.rs | Journal parsing/validation |\n| query_test.rs | run_status/run_history/run_tail |\n| adapter_contract_test.rs | Port implementations (24k lines) |\n| agent_execution_test.rs | BackendResolver, session mgmt (18k lines) |\n| stub_backend_test.rs | StubBackendAdapter behavior |\n\n---\n\n## 9. KEY DESIGN PATTERNS\n\n1. **Ports & Adapters (Hexagonal Architecture)**\n   - Services define trait ports (ProjectStorePort, JournalStorePort, etc.)\n   - Filesystem adapter implements ports\n   - StubBackendAdapter for testing\n\n2. **Atomic Transactional Operations**\n   - Staging directory for project creation\n   - Pending-delete marker for safe project deletion\n   - Write-then-rename for atomicity\n\n3. **Canonical State Over Inference**\n   - RunSnapshot is single source of truth\n   - Journal is durable event log\n   - Payloads/artifacts are historical reference only\n\n4. **Deterministic Rendering**\n   - Payloads must render to identical Markdown for same input\n   - Prevents \"different output, same logic\" bugs\n\n5. **Cascade Configuration Resolution**\n   - Role defaults → Workspace config → Project config → Explicit override\n   - EffectiveConfig resolver handles precedence\n\n6. **Session Reuse Policy**\n   - Not all roles/backends support reuse\n   - SessionPolicy enum controls behavior\n   - SessionManager respects capabilities\n\n---\n\n## 10. PROJECT FILESYSTEM LAYOUT\n\nWhen a project is created, the following structure is initialized:\n\n```\n.ralph-burning/projects/{project_id}/\n├── project.toml                     # Immutable metadata\n├── prompt.md                        # User requirements (immutable reference)\n├── run.json                         # Canonical run state (mutable)\n├── journal.ndjson                   # Durable event log (append-only)\n├── sessions.json                    # Persisted session metadata\n├── history/\n│   ├── payloads/*.json             # Structured stage outputs\n│   └── artifacts/*.json            # Rendered Markdown artifacts\n├── runtime/\n│   ├── backend/*.raw               # Raw backend responses\n│   ├── logs/*.ndjson               # Runtime execution logs\n│   └── temp/                       # Temporary files\n├── amendments/                      # Amendment history\n└── rollback/                        # Rollback point storage\n```\n\n---\n\n## 11. SUMMARY\n\nThe ralph-burning-rewrite is a **well-architected, modular Rust CLI** with:\n\n- **36 Rust source files** across 7 context modules (workflow_composition, project_run_record, agent_execution, workspace_governance, + 3 stubs)\n- **Hexagonal architecture** with clear port definitions and filesystem adapters\n- **Durable state management** using canonical TOML/JSON/NDJSON files\n- **Transactional safety** for project creation/deletion\n- **Deterministic rendering** for stage payloads\n- **16 stage types** across 4 flow presets\n- **3 payload families** (Planning, Execution, Validation) with strict schemas\n- **Comprehensive test coverage** (13 unit test files + CLI integration tests)\n- **StubBackendAdapter** for isolated testing without external dependencies\n\nAll paths listed above are absolute paths from `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/` base directory."}],"totalDurationMs":93179,"totalTokens":74835,"totalToolUseCount":44,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1084,"cache_read_input_tokens":66552,"output_tokens":7193,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1084},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
