{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user provided a feature specification for Loop 6 of the ralph-burning-rewrite project: **\"Standard Preset Run Start Orchestration\"**. The task is to implement the `ralph-burning run start` command that executes the standard flow preset's stages end-to-end using the workflow engine, persisting validated payloads, rendered artifacts, journal events, and run snapshots at durable stage boundaries. The spec includes 17 acceptance criteria covering precondition validation, stage-plan derivation, preflight checks, stage execution through AgentExecutionService, atomic stage commits, failure handling, and comprehensive test coverage (unit, CLI integration, and Gherkin conformance).\n\n   The output format requires an implementation notes markdown file with decisions, deviations, and testing sections.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Hexagonal architecture with ports/adapters pattern\n   - Bounded contexts: workflow_composition, project_run_record, agent_execution, workspace_governance\n   - Atomic stage commit: payload + artifact + journal event + snapshot update as one logical boundary\n   - Preflight validation: check capability + availability for all stages before any mutation\n   - Stage-to-role deterministic mapping (Planner, Implementer, QaValidator, Reviewer, CompletionJudge)\n   - Standard flow stages: PromptReview → Planning → Implementation → Qa → Review → CompletionPanel → AcceptanceQa → FinalReview\n   - Run lifecycle: NotStarted → Running → Completed/Failed\n   - Journal as append-only event log (NDJSON format)\n   - Runtime logs as best-effort, non-durable (cosmetic failures don't affect state)\n   - StubBackendAdapter for testing without real backends\n   - EffectiveConfig cascade resolution for prompt_review.enabled setting\n   - Only `standard` flow supported in this slice; others return UnsupportedFlow error\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs`**\n     - Added 4 new error variants for orchestration\n     ```rust\n     #[error(\"cannot start run: {reason}\")]\n     RunStartFailed { reason: String },\n     #[error(\"flow '{flow_id}' is not yet supported for `run start`; only 'standard' is supported in this slice\")]\n     UnsupportedFlow { flow_id: String },\n     #[error(\"preflight check failed for stage '{stage_id}': {details}\")]\n     PreflightFailed { stage_id: StageId, details: String },\n     #[error(\"stage commit failed for stage '{stage_id}': {details}\")]\n     StageCommitFailed { stage_id: StageId, details: String },\n     ```\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs`**\n     - Added `FailedStageSummary` struct and `Display` impl for `RunStatus`\n     ```rust\n     #[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Serialize, Deserialize)]\n     pub struct FailedStageSummary {\n         pub stage_id: StageId,\n         pub cycle: u32,\n         pub attempt: u32,\n         pub failure_class: String,\n         pub message: String,\n         pub failed_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n     }\n     \n     impl std::fmt::Display for RunStatus {\n         fn fmt(&self, f: &mut std::fmt::Formatter<'_>) -> std::fmt::Result {\n             f.write_str(self.display_str())\n         }\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs`**\n     - Added 5 lifecycle event builder functions: `run_started_event`, `stage_entered_event`, `stage_completed_event` (with `#[allow(clippy::too_many_arguments)]`), `run_completed_event`, `run_failed_event`\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs`**\n     - Added 3 new port traits:\n     ```rust\n     pub trait RunSnapshotWritePort {\n         fn write_run_snapshot(&self, base_dir: &Path, project_id: &ProjectId, snapshot: &RunSnapshot) -> AppResult<()>;\n     }\n     pub trait PayloadArtifactWritePort {\n         fn write_payload_artifact_pair(&self, base_dir: &Path, project_id: &ProjectId, payload: &PayloadRecord, artifact: &ArtifactRecord) -> AppResult<()>;\n     }\n     pub trait RuntimeLogWritePort {\n         fn append_runtime_log(&self, base_dir: &Path, project_id: &ProjectId, entry: &RuntimeLogEntry) -> AppResult<()>;\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/mod.rs`**\n     - Updated exports to include `PayloadArtifactWritePort`, `RunSnapshotWritePort`, `RuntimeLogWritePort`\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs`**\n     - Added 3 new filesystem adapter structs implementing the new ports: `FsRunSnapshotWriteStore`, `FsPayloadArtifactWriteStore` (with rollback on artifact write failure), `FsRuntimeLogWriteStore`\n     - Updated import to include new port traits\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs`** (NEW FILE - core of this loop)\n     - The main orchestration engine with:\n       - `standard_stage_plan(prompt_review_enabled: bool) -> Vec<StageId>` - derives executable stages\n       - `role_for_stage(stage_id: StageId) -> BackendRole` - deterministic mapping\n       - `StagePlan` struct with stage_id, role, contract, target\n       - `resolve_stage_plan()` - resolves backend targets for all stages\n       - `preflight_check()` - validates capability + availability before any mutation\n       - `execute_standard_run()` - main orchestration loop (marked `#[allow(clippy::too_many_arguments)]`)\n       - `fail_run()` - helper to record failure in journal + snapshot (marked `#[allow(clippy::too_many_arguments)]`)\n     - The engine: validates preconditions → derives stage plan → resolves targets → preflight checks → generates run ID → persists run_started → loops through stages (stage_entered → invoke → evaluate contract → persist payload/artifact → stage_completed → update snapshot) → persists run_completed\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/mod.rs`**\n     - Added `pub mod engine;`\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/agent_execution/service.rs`**\n     - Added `adapter()` method to expose the adapter for preflight checks:\n     ```rust\n     pub fn adapter(&self) -> &A {\n         &self.adapter\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs`** (REWRITTEN)\n     - Replaced `NotYetImplemented` stub for `run start` with full `handle_start()` implementation\n     - Validates workspace version, active project, project record, flow type (standard only), run snapshot integrity\n     - Calls `engine::execute_standard_run()` with all required adapter instances\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs`** (NEW FILE)\n     - Tests: stage_plan_with_prompt_review_enabled, stage_plan_with_prompt_review_disabled, role_mapping_is_deterministic\n     - Async tests: happy_path_standard_run_completes, happy_path_prompt_review_disabled, run_start_rejects_already_running, run_start_rejects_completed_project, preflight_failure_leaves_state_unchanged, preflight_check_succeeds_with_default_stub, preflight_check_fails_with_unavailable_backend, resolve_stage_plan_produces_correct_targets\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit.rs`**\n     - Added `workflow_engine_test` module registration\n\n   - **`ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/project_run_record_test.rs`**\n     - Added tests: failed_stage_summary_serializes_correctly, run_status_display_matches_display_str, run_snapshot_completed_has_no_active_run, run_snapshot_failed_has_no_active_run\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **`cargo check` failed**: `no method named 'read_run_snapshot' found for struct 'FsRunSnapshotStore'` in cli/run.rs:88. Fixed by adding `RunSnapshotPort` to the import: `use crate::contexts::project_run_record::service::{self, ProjectStorePort, RunSnapshotPort};`\n   - **`cargo clippy` failed with 3 errors**: `too_many_arguments` on `stage_completed_event` (8 args), `execute_standard_run` (9 args), `fail_run` (9 args). Fixed by adding `#[allow(clippy::too_many_arguments)]` to each function.\n   - **Test compilation failed**: `no method named 'write_run_snapshot' found for struct 'FsRunSnapshotWriteStore'` in tests. Fixed by adding `RunSnapshotWritePort` to imports and cleaning up unused imports (`journal`, `JournalEvent`, `ProjectStorePort`).\n   - **Build environment**: `cargo` command not found initially. Discovered nix store paths needed to be used directly. Also needed `cc` linker - found gcc wrapper in nix store.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Solved the architecture for preflight checks: initially tried an `InternalAdapter` wrapper pattern, then simplified to adding an `adapter()` method on `AgentExecutionService` to directly expose the backend adapter for preflight capability/availability checks.\n   - Solved atomic stage commit: payload written first, then artifact. If artifact write fails, payload is cleaned up. If journal append fails after payload/artifact, error is returned with StageCommitFailed.\n   - Build environment discovery: found cargo at `/nix/store/yqcsaywfvcyy9wmbzb5fawp29icgi7cb-cargo-1.92.0/bin/cargo`, gcc at `/nix/store/kbw2j1vag664b3sj3rjwz9v53cqx87sb-gcc-wrapper-15.2.0/bin/cc`, clippy at `/nix/store/zmrbcbd77w6nylgwyagnxh87all5swjf-clippy-1.92.0/bin/cargo-clippy`.\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - **Message 1**: The full feature specification for Loop 6, including system guardrails, the spec itself (acceptance criteria, files to modify/create, dependencies), review feedback (none), and the master prompt describing the entire ralph-burning v1 rewrite project. Instructs to implement the spec, verify compilation, and output implementation notes.\n   - **Message 2**: \"Tool loaded.\" (after TodoWrite tool was fetched)\n   - **Message 3**: Current request for a detailed conversation summary.\n\n7. Pending Tasks (from the todo list):\n   - Add CLI integration tests for `run start` (tests/cli.rs)\n   - Add Gherkin conformance feature (tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature)\n   - Run final `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` to verify everything passes\n   - Write the implementation notes output file (`<TS>-impl-notes.md`)\n   - Tests have NOT been run yet (only `cargo check` and `cargo clippy` have passed)\n\n8. Current Work:\n   I had just finished extending `tests/unit/project_run_record_test.rs` with 4 new tests (failed_stage_summary_serializes_correctly, run_status_display_matches_display_str, run_snapshot_completed_has_no_active_run, run_snapshot_failed_has_no_active_run). The todo list shows:\n   - \"Add/extend unit tests for project_run_record\" was marked in_progress\n   - \"Add CLI integration tests for run start\" was pending\n   - \"Add Gherkin conformance feature\" was pending  \n   - \"Run cargo check and cargo clippy, fix errors\" was pending\n   \n   I had not yet run `cargo test` to verify all tests pass. The most recent successful compilation check was `cargo check --all-targets` which passed.\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Continue with the remaining pending tasks from the todo list. The immediate next step is to add CLI integration tests for `run start` in `tests/cli.rs`, then create the Gherkin conformance feature at `tests/conformance/features/run_start_standard.feature`, then run `cargo test` and `cargo clippy --all-targets --all-features -- -D warnings` to verify everything passes, and finally produce the `<TS>-impl-notes.md` output as specified in the task format. The build command requires these PATH entries: `export PATH=\"/nix/store/kbw2j1vag664b3sj3rjwz9v53cqx87sb-gcc-wrapper-15.2.0/bin:/nix/store/zmrbcbd77w6nylgwyagnxh87all5swjf-clippy-1.92.0/bin:$PATH\"` and cargo at `/nix/store/yqcsaywfvcyy9wmbzb5fawp29icgi7cb-cargo-1.92.0/bin/cargo`.\n\nIf you need specific details from before compaction (li