{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YG3bbcj5FVEzgQhMTjQmhs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Feature: Run Queries\n     2→  Canonical run status, durable history, and runtime-log separation.\n     3→\n     4→  # SC-RUN-001\n     5→  Scenario: Run status reports \"not started\" for a new project\n     6→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n     7→    And project \"alpha\" has no active run\n     8→    When the user runs \"run status\"\n     9→    Then the output includes \"not started\"\n    10→    And the status is read from canonical run state, not inferred from artifacts\n    11→\n    12→  # SC-RUN-002\n    13→  Scenario: Run status reports active run with stage cursor\n    14→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" that has an active run\n    15→    When the user runs \"run status\"\n    16→    Then the output includes run status, current stage, cycle, and completion round\n    17→    And the status is derived from canonical run.json, not artifact scans\n    18→\n    19→  # SC-RUN-003\n    20→  Scenario: Run history shows durable history only\n    21→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n    22→    And project \"alpha\" has journal events and payload/artifact records\n    23→    When the user runs \"run history\"\n    24→    Then the output includes journal events in canonical order\n    25→    And the output includes payload and artifact records\n    26→    And the output does not include runtime logs\n    27→\n    28→  # SC-RUN-004\n    29→  Scenario: Run history never includes runtime logs\n    30→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" that has runtime logs\n    31→    When the user runs \"run history\"\n    32→    Then the output does not contain any runtime log entries\n    33→\n    34→  # SC-RUN-005\n    35→  Scenario: Run tail shows durable history only by default\n    36→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n    37→    When the user runs \"run tail\"\n    38→    Then the output includes durable history (journal events)\n    39→    And the output does not include a runtime logs section\n    40→\n    41→  # SC-RUN-006\n    42→  Scenario: Run tail --logs appends runtime logs after durable history\n    43→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n    44→    And project \"alpha\" has runtime logs\n    45→    When the user runs \"run tail --logs\"\n    46→    Then the output includes durable history section\n    47→    And the output includes a runtime logs section after the durable section\n    48→    And the durable history portion is unchanged compared to \"run tail\" without --logs\n    49→\n    50→  # SC-RUN-007\n    51→  Scenario: Corrupt canonical files fail fast with file-specific errors\n    52→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    53→    And \"run.json\" for project \"alpha\" contains invalid JSON\n    54→    When the user runs \"run status\"\n    55→    Then the command fails with error referencing \"run.json\"\n    56→    And the command does not fall back to Markdown or directory scans\n    57→\n    58→  # SC-RUN-008\n    59→  Scenario: Corrupt journal fails fast\n    60→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    61→    And \"journal.ndjson\" for project \"alpha\" contains a sequence gap\n    62→    When the user runs \"run history\"\n    63→    Then the command fails with error containing \"journal sequence\"\n    64→\n    65→  # SC-RUN-009\n    66→  Scenario: Orphaned artifact record fails consistency check\n    67→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    68→    And project \"alpha\" has an artifact referencing a non-existent payload\n    69→    When the user runs \"run history\"\n    70→    Then the command fails with error containing \"does not exist\"\n    71→\n    72→  # SC-RUN-010\n    73→  Scenario: Runtime log write failures do not affect durable history\n    74→    Given runtime log writes are failing\n    75→    When durable history is queried via \"run history\"\n    76→    Then durable history records are returned intact\n    77→    And no durable history records are fabricated, removed, or reordered\n    78→\n    79→  # SC-RUN-011\n    80→  Scenario: Missing run.json fails fast\n    81→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    82→    And \"run.json\" for project \"alpha\" has been deleted\n    83→    When the user runs \"run status\"\n    84→    Then the command fails with error referencing \"run.json\" and \"missing\"\n    85→\n    86→  # SC-RUN-012\n    87→  Scenario: Missing journal.ndjson fails fast\n    88→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    89→    And \"journal.ndjson\" for project \"alpha\" has been deleted\n    90→    When the user runs \"run history\"\n    91→    Then the command fails with error referencing \"journal.ndjson\" and \"missing\"\n    92→\n    93→  # SC-RUN-013\n    94→  Scenario: Orphaned payload record fails consistency check\n    95→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    96→    And project \"alpha\" has a payload with no matching artifact\n    97→    When the user runs \"run history\"\n    98→    Then the command fails with error containing \"no matching artifact\"\n    99→\n   100→  # SC-RUN-014\n   101→  Scenario: Run tail includes payload and artifact records in durable section\n   102→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" that has payload and artifact records\n   103→    When the user runs \"run tail\"\n   104→    Then the durable section includes payload and artifact records\n   105→    And the output matches what \"run history\" would show for the same data\n   106→\n   107→  # SC-RUN-015\n   108→  Scenario: Run status reports terminal completed state without active run\n   109→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n   110→    And \"run.json\" for project \"alpha\" contains status \"completed\" with active_run null\n   111→    When the user runs \"run status\"\n   112→    Then the output includes \"completed\"\n   113→    And the output does not include \"not started\"\n   114→\n   115→  # SC-RUN-016\n   116→  Scenario: Run status reports terminal failed state without active run\n   117→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n   118→    And \"run.json\" for project \"alpha\" contains status \"failed\" with active_run null\n   119→    When the user runs \"run status\"\n   120→    Then the output includes \"failed\"\n   121→    And the output does not include \"not started\"\n   122→\n   123→  # SC-RUN-017\n   124→  Scenario: Semantically inconsistent run.json fails fast\n   125→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n   126→    And \"run.json\" for project \"alpha\" contains status \"running\" with active_run null\n   127→    When the user runs \"run status\"\n   128→    Then the command fails with error referencing \"run.json\" and \"inconsistent\"\n   129→\n   130→  # SC-RUN-018\n   131→  Scenario: Project delete fails for semantically inconsistent paused snapshot\n   132→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n   133→    And \"run.json\" for project \"alpha\" contains status \"paused\" with active_run null\n   134→    When the user runs \"project delete alpha\"\n   135→    Then the command fails with error referencing \"run.json\" and \"inconsistent\"\n   136→\n   137→  # SC-RUN-019\n   138→  Scenario: Run status fails fast when active project has corrupt project.toml\n   139→    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n   140→    And \"project.toml\" for project \"alpha\" contains malformed content\n   141→    When the user runs \"run status\"\n   142→    Then the command fails with error referencing \"project.toml\"\n   143→\n  