{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VwuMdbo4Yfw9qb7NhghzrF","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile the final report:\n\n## Ralph Burning Rewrite - Complete Code Exploration Report\n\n### Project Structure Overview\n\nThe ralph-burning-rewrite project is organized into a Rust binary with comprehensive bounded contexts following Clean Architecture principles. Here's the directory tree:\n\n```\n/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main.rs                          # Entry point\n│   ├── lib.rs                           # Library root\n│   ├── adapters/                        # External integration\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── fs.rs                        # Filesystem persistence layer (37 implementations)\n│   │   └── stub_backend.rs              # Test backend adapter\n│   ├── cli/                             # Command-line interface\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── run.rs                       # Run subcommand (start, status, history, tail)\n│   │   ├── project.rs\n│   │   ├── init.rs\n│   │   ├── config.rs\n│   │   ├── flow.rs\n│   │   ├── conformance.rs\n│   │   ├── daemon.rs\n│   │   └── requirements.rs\n│   ├── contexts/                        # Bounded contexts (DDD)\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── agent_execution/             # Backend invocation management\n│   │   │   ├── model.rs\n│   │   │   ├── service.rs\n│   │   │   └── session.rs\n│   │   ├── project_run_record/          # Core project/run state management\n│   │   │   ├── model.rs                 # Data models\n│   │   │   ├── service.rs               # Use case implementations\n│   │   │   ├── journal.rs               # Event journaling\n│   │   │   ├── queries.rs\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── workflow_composition/        # Stage orchestration\n│   │   │   ├── engine.rs                # Main execution engine\n│   │   │   ├── contracts.rs             # Stage contracts & validation\n│   │   │   ├── payloads.rs              # Typed payload models\n│   │   │   ├── renderers.rs             # Markdown artifact generation\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── workspace_governance/        # Workspace/project configuration\n│   │   │   ├── config.rs\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── automation_runtime/\n│   │   ├── conformance_spec/\n│   │   └── requirements_drafting/\n│   └── shared/                          # Cross-cutting concerns\n│       ├── domain.rs                    # Domain value objects & enums\n│       ├── error.rs                     # Error types & handling\n│       └── mod.rs\n├── tests/unit/                          # Comprehensive test suite\n│   ├── workflow_engine_test.rs\n│   ├── project_run_record_test.rs\n│   └── [11 other test files]\n├── Cargo.toml\n└── Cargo.lock\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. Engine.rs (Workflow Composition Engine)\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs`\n\n**Purpose:** Core orchestration engine that executes the standard delivery flow from start to completion.\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n- **`standard_stage_plan(prompt_review_enabled: bool) -> Vec<StageId>`**\n  - Derives executable stage sequence from FlowPreset::Standard\n  - Optionally filters out PromptReview stage based on config\n  - Returns 8 stages with prompt_review=true, 7 without\n\n- **`role_for_stage(stage_id: StageId) -> BackendRole`**\n  - Maps each stage to a single deterministic backend role\n  - Delegates to `BackendRole::for_stage(stage_id)`\n\n- **`resolve_stage_plan(...) -> AppResult<Vec<StagePlan>>`**\n  - Resolves all stage targets ahead of execution\n  - Preflight validation structure with role, contract, and target per stage\n\n- **`preflight_check<A: AgentExecutionPort>(...) -> AppResult<()>`**\n  - Validates capability and availability for every stage target\n  - Fails fast before any state mutation\n\n- **`execute_standard_run<A, R, S>(...) -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Main state machine with 8-step progression:\n    1. Read current snapshot and validate preconditions\n    2. Derive stage plan with prompt_review config\n    3. Resolve backend targets for every stage\n    4. Preflight checks (all-or-nothing)\n    5. Generate run ID and read journal for sequence tracking\n    6. Persist run_started event + snapshot with Running status\n    7. Execute stages in canonical order (loop with error handling)\n    8. Mark run as Completed or Failed atomically\n  \n  - **Stage Execution Loop:**\n    - Emits `stage_entered` event\n    - Updates cursor in snapshot\n    - Logs to runtime logs\n    - Invokes backend with InvocationRequest (timeout, cancellation token, session policy)\n    - Evaluates contract: schema validation → semantic validation → rendering\n    - Persists payload + artifact pair atomically\n    - Emits `stage_completed` event\n    - Updates snapshot with next stage cursor\n    - On failure: calls `fail_run()`, returns error\n\n- **`fail_run(...) -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Records run failure with failure_class\n  - Persists `run_failed` event\n  - Updates snapshot to Failed status\n  - Returns AppError::RunStartFailed\n\n**Helper:**\n- **`generate_run_id() -> AppResult<RunId>`** - Timestamp-based run ID generation\n- **`project_root_path(base_dir, project_id) -> PathBuf`** - Standard path construction\n\n---\n\n### 2. Domain.rs (Shared Domain Model)\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs`\n\n**Key Enums & Stage-to-Role Mapping:**\n\n**BackendFamily** (4 variants):\n```\n- Claude       → \"opus-4.1\" (Planner default)\n- Codex        → \"gpt-5-codex\" (Implementer default)\n- OpenRouter   → \"openai/gpt-5\" (QaValidator default)\n- Stub         → \"stub-default\" (Testing)\n```\n\n**BackendRole** (5 variants):\n```\npub fn for_stage(stage_id: StageId) -> Self {\n    match stage_id {\n        PromptReview | Planning | DocsPlan | CiPlan => Planner,\n        Implementation | PlanAndImplement | ApplyFixes | DocsUpdate | CiUpdate => Implementer,\n        Qa | DocsValidation | CiValidation | AcceptanceQa => QaValidator,\n        Review | FinalReview => Reviewer,\n        CompletionPanel => CompletionJudge,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Default Targets by Role:**\n- Planner → Claude opus-4.1\n- Implementer → Codex gpt-5-codex\n- Reviewer → Claude sonnet-4.0\n- QaValidator → OpenRouter openai/gpt-5\n- CompletionJudge → Claude opus-4.1\n\n**StageId** (16 variants):\n- **Planning stages:** PromptReview, Planning, DocsPlan, CiPlan\n- **Execution stages:** Implementation, PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsUpdate, CiUpdate\n- **Validation stages:** Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview, DocsValidation, CiValidation\n\n**FlowPreset** (4 variants):\n- Standard (8 stages: prompt_review → planning → implementation → qa → review → completion_panel → acceptance_qa → final_review)\n- QuickDev (4 stages: plan_and_implement → review → apply_fixes → final_review)\n- DocsChange (4 stages: docs_plan → docs_update → docs_validation → review)\n- CiImprovement (4 stages: ci_plan → ci_update → ci_validation → review)\n\n**StageCursor:**\n```rust\npub struct StageCursor {\n    pub stage: StageId,\n    pub cycle: u32,      // >= 1\n    pub attempt: u32,    // >= 1\n    pub completion_round: u32,  // >= 1\n}\n```\n- Encodes position within multi-cycle/attempt execution\n- Immutable once created; movements create new cursors\n\n**ProjectId & RunId:** Newtype wrappers with validation (non-empty, single path segment)\n\n**FailureClass:** (6 variants) TransportFailure, SchemaValidationFailure, DomainValidationFailure, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailure\n\n**ResolvedBackendTarget:**\n```rust\npub struct ResolvedBackendTarget {\n    pub backend: BackendSpec,\n    pub model: ModelSpec,\n}\n```\n- Resolved configuration with capability checks\n- Supports session reuse, structured output, cancellation per backend\n\n---\n\n### 3. Project Run Record (State Management)\n\n#### Model (`model.rs`)\n\n**RunSnapshot** (canonical state in `run.json`):\n```rust\npub struct RunSnapshot {\n    pub active_run: Option<ActiveRun>,        // Current execution context\n    pub status: RunStatus,                    // NotStarted | Running | Paused | Completed | Failed\n    pub cycle_history: Vec<CycleHistoryEntry>,\n    pub completion_rounds: u32,\n    pub rollback_point_meta: RollbackPointMeta,\n    pub amendment_queue: AmendmentQueueState,\n    pub status_summary: String,               // Human-readable status\n}\n\npub struct ActiveRun {\n    pub run_id: String,\n    pub stage_cursor: StageCursor,\n    pub started_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n}\n```\n\n**Semantic Validation Rules:**\n- RunStatus::Running/Paused **requires** Some(active_run)\n- RunStatus::NotStarted **requires** None active_run\n- RunStatus::Completed/Failed **allows** either\n\n**JournalEvent** (stored in `journal.ndjson`, one per line):\n```rust\npub struct JournalEvent {\n    pub sequence: u64,                        // Monotonic, starts at 1\n    pub timestamp: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub event_type: JournalEventType,\n    pub details: serde_json::Value,\n}\n\npub enum JournalEventType {\n    ProjectCreated,      // Sequence 1\n    RunStarted,\n    StageEntered,\n    StageCompleted,      // Details: { run_id, stage_id, cycle, attempt, payload_id, artifact_id }\n    CycleAdvanced,\n    CompletionRoundAdvanced,\n    RunCompleted,\n    RunFailed,           // Details: { run_id, stage_id, failure_class, message }\n    RollbackCreated,\n    AmendmentQueued,\n}\n```\n\n**PayloadRecord** (stored in `history/payloads/{payload_id}.json`):\n```rust\npub struct PayloadRecord {\n    pub payload_id: String,                   // {run_id}-{stage_id}-c{cycle}-a{attempt}\n    pub stage_id: StageId,\n    pub cycle: u32,\n    pub attempt: u32,\n    pub created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub payload: serde_json::Value,           // Validated StagePayload as JSON\n}\n```\n\n**ArtifactRecord** (stored in `history/artifacts/{artifact_id}.json`):\n```rust\npub struct ArtifactRecord {\n    pub artifact_id: String,                  // {payload_id}-artifact\n    pub payload_id: String,\n    pub stage_id: StageId,\n    pub created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub content: String,                      // Markdown artifact\n}\n```\n\n**RuntimeLogEntry** (stored in `runtime/logs/run.ndjson`):\n```rust\npub struct RuntimeLogEntry {\n    pub timestamp: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub level: LogLevel,                      // Debug | Info | Warn | Error\n    pub source: String,                       // e.g., \"engine\"\n    pub message: String,\n}\n```\n\n#### Service (`service.rs`)\n\n**Ports (traits for adapter implementation):**\n\n- **ProjectStorePort:** project_exists, read_project_record, list_project_ids, stage_delete, commit_delete, rollback_delete, create_project_atomic\n- **JournalStorePort:** read_journal, append_event\n- **ArtifactStorePort:** list_payloads, list_artifacts\n- **RuntimeLogStorePort:** read_runtime_logs\n- **RunSnapshotPort:** read_run_snapshot\n- **RunSnapshotWritePort:** write_run_snapshot (atomic)\n- **PayloadArtifactWritePort:** write_payload_artifact_pair (atomic pair)\n- **RuntimeLogWritePort:** append_runtime_log (best-effort)\n- **ActiveProjectPort:** read_active_project_id, clear_active_project, write_active_project\n\n**Use Cases:**\n\n- **`create_project(...) -> AppResult<ProjectRecord>`**\n  - Validates no duplicate project ID\n  - Creates record, initial snapshot, journal event\n  - Calls `store.create_project_atomic()` (all-or-nothing)\n\n- **`list_projects(...) -> AppResult<Vec<ProjectListEntry>>`**\n  - Reads all project IDs\n  - Enriches with active flag and metadata\n\n- **`show_project(...) -> AppResult<ProjectDetail>`**\n  - Reads record, snapshot, journal events\n  - Counts rollback points from journal\n  - Returns full detail view\n\n- **`delete_project(...) -> AppResult<()>`** (Transactional)\n  - Validates no active run\n  - Phase 1: stage_delete (project invisible but data remains)\n  - Phase 2: clear_active_project if was active (with rollback on failure)\n  - Phase 3: commit_delete (permanent removal, best-effort)\n\n- **`run_status(...) -> AppResult<RunStatusView>`**\n  - Queries current run status from snapshot\n  - Delegates to queries module\n\n- **`run_history(...) -> AppResult<RunHistoryView>`**\n  - Reads durable journal, payloads, artifacts\n  - Validates history consistency\n  - Returns structured history view\n\n- **`run_tail(...) -> AppResult<RunTailView>`**\n  - Durable history by default\n  - Optionally includes runtime logs\n  - Returns tail view for recent progress\n\n#### Journal (`journal.rs`)\n\n**Event Builders:**\n```rust\npub fn run_started_event(sequence, timestamp, run_id, first_stage) -> JournalEvent\npub fn stage_entered_event(sequence, timestamp, run_id, stage_id, cycle, attempt) -> JournalEvent\npub fn stage_completed_event(sequence, ..., payload_id, artifact_id) -> JournalEvent\npub fn run_completed_event(sequence, ..., completion_rounds) -> JournalEvent\npub fn run_failed_event(sequence, ..., stage_id, failure_class, message) -> JournalEvent\n```\n\n**Parsing & Validation:**\n- **`parse_journal(contents: &str) -> AppResult<Vec<JournalEvent>>`**\n  - Parses NDJSON line-by-line\n  - Validates monotonic sequence (first must be 1)\n  - Ensures first event is ProjectCreated\n  - Returns parsed, validated events in order\n\n- **`validate_sequence(last_sequence, event) -> AppResult<()>`**\n  - Enforces event.sequence == last_sequence + 1\n\n- **`last_sequence(events) -> u64`**\n  - Returns last sequence number or 0 if empty\n\n---\n\n### 4. Adapters/fs.rs (Filesystem Persistence)\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` (700 lines, 37 implementations)\n\n**Key Constants:**\n- WORKSPACE_DIR = \".ralph-burning\"\n- PROJECTS_DIR = \"projects\"\n- PROJECT_SUBDIRS = [\"history/payloads\", \"history/artifacts\", \"runtime/logs\", \"runtime/backend\", \"runtime/temp\", \"amendments\", \"rollback\"]\n\n**FileSystem (Static Utility Class):**\n\n- **`create_workspace(workspace_root, config, directories) -> AppResult<()>`**\n  - Creates workspace directory structure\n  - Writes workspace.toml atomically\n\n- **`write_atomic(path, contents) -> AppResult<()>`**\n  - Two-phase: write to temp file, fsync, atomic rename\n  - Timestamp-based temp naming to prevent collisions\n  - Cleans up temp file on failure\n\n- **`read_to_string(path) -> AppResult<String>`**\n- **`prompt_hash(contents) -> String`** - DefaultHasher-based hash\n- **`open_editor(path) -> AppResult<()>`** - Spawns EDITOR or VISUAL environment variable\n\n**Implementations (8 structs × 4-5 ports each):**\n\n1. **FsProjectStore** (ProjectStorePort)\n   - project_exists: checks project root + project.toml\n   - read_project_record: TOML deserialization\n   - list_project_ids: reads projects dir, skips hidden (staging/trash)\n   - stage_delete: atomic rename to `.{id}.pending-delete`\n   - commit_delete: removes pending-delete directory\n   - rollback_delete: renames pending-delete back to canonical path\n   - create_project_atomic: staging + atomic rename pattern\n\n2. **FsJournalStore** (JournalStorePort)\n   - read_journal: reads `journal.ndjson` and parses\n   - append_event: appends line with newline\n\n3. **FsArtifactStore** (ArtifactStorePort)\n   - list_payloads: reads `history/payloads/*.json`, sorts by created_at\n   - list_artifacts: reads `history/artifacts/*.json`, sorts by created_at\n\n4. **FsRuntimeLogStore** (RuntimeLogStorePort)\n   - read_runtime_logs: reads only newest `runtime/logs/*.ndjson` file\n\n5. **FsRunSnapshotStore** (RunSnapshotPort)\n   - read_run_snapshot: JSON deserialization + semantic validation\n\n6. **FsRunSnapshotWriteStore** (RunSnapshotWritePort)\n   - write_run_snapshot: pretty JSON via write_atomic\n\n7. **FsPayloadArtifactWriteStore** (PayloadArtifactWritePort)\n   - write_payload_artifact_pair: writes payload, then artifact (removes payload on artifact failure)\n\n8. **FsRuntimeLogWriteStore** (RuntimeLogWritePort)\n   - append_runtime_log: NDJSON append to `runtime/logs/run.ndjson`\n\n9. **FsActiveProjectStore** (ActiveProjectPort)\n   - read_active_project_id: reads `active-project` file\n   - clear_active_project: removes `active-project` file\n   - write_active_project: writes project ID via write_atomic\n\n10. **FsRawOutputStore** (RawOutputPort)\n    - persist_raw_output: writes to `runtime/backend/{invocation_id}.raw`\n\n11. **FsSessionStore** (SessionStorePort)\n    - load_sessions: reads `sessions.json`\n    - save_sessions: writes `sessions.json` atomically\n\n---\n\n### 5. Error.rs (Error Handling)\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs`\n\n**AppError Enum** (23 variants, all `#[error(...)]`):\n- AlreadyInitialized, WorkspaceConflict\n- InvalidStageCursorField, InvalidIdentifier, InvalidFlowPreset\n- UnsupportedWorkspaceVersion, UnknownConfigKey, InvalidConfigValue\n- NoActiveProject, ProjectNotFound, EditorFailed, DuplicateProject\n- CorruptRecord, InvalidPrompt, ActiveRunDelete\n- JournalSequence, RunStartFailed, UnsupportedFlow\n- PreflightFailed, StageCommitFailed, NotYetImplemented\n- BackendUnavailable, CapabilityMismatch, InvocationFailed, InvocationTimeout, InvocationCancelled\n- Io, TomlDeserialize, TomlSerialize, TomlEdit, SerdeJson\n\n**ContractError Enum** (4 variants):\n- SchemaValidation { stage_id, details }\n- DomainValidation { stage_id, details }\n- RenderError { stage_id, details }\n- QaReviewOutcome { stage_id, outcome }\n\n**Methods:**\n- `impl ContractError: failure_class() -> FailureClass, stage_id() -> StageId`\n- `impl AppError: failure_class() -> Option<FailureClass>`\n\n---\n\n### 6. CLI run.rs (Run Subcommand)\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs`\n\n**RunSubcommand Enum:**\n- Start - Execute standard run\n- Resume - Not yet implemented\n- Status - Report current run state\n- History - List durable journal events + payloads/artifacts\n- Tail { logs: bool } - Recent progress + optional runtime logs\n- Rollback { to: String, hard: bool } - Not yet implemented\n\n**Handlers:**\n\n- **`handle_start() -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Validate workspace version\n  - Resolve active project ID\n  - Read project record\n  - Enforce FlowPreset::Standard only\n  - Read run snapshot\n  - Validate preconditions (status == NotStarted, no active run)\n  - Load effective config\n  - Call engine::execute_standard_run with all port implementations\n  - Print completion message\n\n- **`handle_status() -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Load workspace config\n  - Resolve active project\n  - Call service::run_status\n  - Print status summary\n\n- **`handle_history() -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Resolve active project\n  - Call service::run_history\n  - Print journal events, payloads, artifacts\n\n- **`handle_tail(include_logs: bool) -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Resolve active project\n  - Call service::run_tail\n  - Print durable history + optional runtime logs\n\n- **`build_agent_execution_service() -> AgentExecutionService<StubBackendAdapter, FsRawOutputStore, FsSessionStore>`**\n  - Default service builder using stub backend for testing\n\n---\n\n### 7. Test Files\n\n#### workflow_engine_test.rs (389 lines)\n\n**Stage Plan Tests:**\n- `stage_plan_with_prompt_review_enabled()` - Asserts 8 stages\n- `stage_plan_with_prompt_review_disabled()` - Asserts 7 stages, no PromptReview\n- `role_mapping_is_deterministic()` - Validates all 8 stage-to-role mappings\n\n**Happy Path Tests:**\n- `happy_path_standard_run_completes()` - Full end-to-end execution\n  - Asserts status == Completed, active_run is None\n  - Verifies >= 19 journal events (project_created + run_started + 16 stage events + run_completed)\n  - Confirms 8 payloads, 8 artifacts written\n\n- `happy_path_prompt_review_disabled()` - Standard run without prompt_review\n  - Asserts 7 payloads, no prompt_review stage_entered events\n\n**Precondition Failure Tests:**\n- `run_start_rejects_already_running()` - Fails if status != NotStarted\n- `run_start_rejects_completed_project()` - Fails if status == Completed\n\n**Preflight Failure Tests:**\n- `preflight_failure_leaves_state_unchanged()` - Uses unavailable backend\n  - Verifies snapshot still NotStarted\n  - Verifies journal only has project_created\n  - Verifies no payloads/artifacts created\n\n**Plan Resolution Tests:**\n- `resolve_stage_plan_produces_correct_targets()` - 8 stages resolved correctly\n- `preflight_check_succeeds_with_default_stub()` - Default adapter passes\n- `preflight_check_fails_with_unavailable_backend()` - Fails as expected\n\n#### project_run_record_test.rs (840 lines)\n\n**Domain Tests:**\n- `run_snapshot_initial_has_no_active_run()` - Initial state validation\n- `session_store_empty_has_no_sessions()` - Empty store\n- `project_record_flow_is_immutable_after_creation()` - Immutability\n- `journal_event_types_serialize_to_snake_case()` - Serde format\n\n**Service Tests with Fake Ports:**\n- `create_project_succeeds_with_valid_input()` - Success path\n- `create_project_fails_on_duplicate_id()` - Duplicate rejection\n- `list_projects_returns_entries_with_active_flag()` - List with active marking\n- `list_projects_with_no_active_project()` - No active case\n- `show_project_returns_detail()` - Detail view\n- `show_project_fails_for_missing_project()` - Missing project error\n- `delete_project_succeeds_when_no_active_run()` - Deletion success\n- `delete_project_fails_with_active_run()` - Active run blocks deletion\n- `delete_project_fails_for_missing_project()` - Missing project error\n- `run_status_reports_not_started_when_no_active_run()` - Status reporting\n- `run_status_reports_running_with_stage_cursor()` - Running status with cursor\n\n**Semantic Validation Tests:**\n- `run_snapshot_validates_running_without_active_run_as_corrupt()` - Corruption detection\n- `run_snapshot_validates_paused_without_active_run_as_corrupt()`\n- `run_snapshot_validates_not_started_with_active_run_as_corrupt()`\n- `run_snapshot_validates_completed_without_active_run_as_valid()` - Valid terminal state\n- `run_snapshot_validates_failed_without_active_run_as_valid()`\n\n**Transactional Delete Tests:**\n- `delete_project_does_not_touch_pointer_on_stage_failure()` - Rollback on stage failure\n- `delete_project_rolls_back_on_clear_pointer_failure()` - Rollback on clear failure\n- `delete_project_succeeds_for_completed_terminal_state()` - Terminal state deletion\n\n**Model Serialization Tests:**\n- `failed_stage_summary_serializes_correctly()` - JSON roundtrip\n- `run_status_display_matches_display_str()` - Display trait\n- `run_snapshot_completed_has_no_active_run()` - Terminal state invariants\n- `run_snapshot_failed_has_no_active_run()`\n\n---\n\n### Key Architectural Patterns\n\n1. **Port & Adapter Pattern:** All persistence operations are abstract through traits (ports) with concrete filesystem implementations (adapters)\n\n2. **Bounded Contexts:** Clear separation:\n   - workflow_composition (orchestration)\n   - project_run_record (state management)\n   - agent_execution (backend interaction)\n   - workspace_governance (configuration)\n\n3. **Transactional Operations:**\n   - Atomic file writes with temp file + rename pattern\n   - Staging directory for project creation\n   - Multi-phase delete with rollback semantics\n\n4. **Deterministic Flow:**\n   - Stage → Role mapping is fixed in BackendRole::for_stage\n   - Flow definitions are constants\n   - Journal sequence is monotonic and validated\n\n5. **Contract-Driven Validation:**\n   - Three payload families (Planning, Execution, Validation)\n   - Schema → Semantic → Outcome → Rendering pipeline\n   - Each stage maps to exactly one contract\n\n6. **Error Classification:**\n   - FailureClass enums for retry/terminal policy decisions\n   - ContractError maps to FailureClass deterministically\n   - AppError has optional failure_class for context\n\n---\n\n### File Paths Summary\n\n**Critical Files:**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` - Main orchestration\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` - Domain model & stage-to-role mapping\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` - State models\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs` - Use cases\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs` - Event journaling\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` - Filesystem layer (37 implementations)\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` - Error handling\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` - CLI run subcommand\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs` - Engine tests\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/project_run_record_test.rs` - State management tests\n\n**Total Source Files:** 37 Rust files across contexts, adapters, CLI, and shared modules"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a68e5c17230bca1ff (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 91717\ntool_uses: 27\nduration_ms: 96809</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"19a33b10-b5a0-4ba2-8943-a7efa3e34818","uuid":"d0deda2a-b7b3-47a8-ada5-40dd6dc46489","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the ralph-burning-rewrite directory structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The full directory tree of src/ and tests/\n2. The current engine.rs implementation (workflow_composition)\n3. The shared/domain.rs file (especially stage-to-role mapping)\n4. The project_run_record service, model, and journal files\n5. The adapters/fs.rs file\n6. The shared/error.rs file\n7. The CLI run.rs file\n8. The test files for workflow_engine_test.rs and project_run_record_test.rs\n\nRead all of these files completely. This is a \"very thorough\" exploration.","agentId":"a68e5c17230bca1ff","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me compile the final report:\n\n## Ralph Burning Rewrite - Complete Code Exploration Report\n\n### Project Structure Overview\n\nThe ralph-burning-rewrite project is organized into a Rust binary with comprehensive bounded contexts following Clean Architecture principles. Here's the directory tree:\n\n```\n/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main.rs                          # Entry point\n│   ├── lib.rs                           # Library root\n│   ├── adapters/                        # External integration\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── fs.rs                        # Filesystem persistence layer (37 implementations)\n│   │   └── stub_backend.rs              # Test backend adapter\n│   ├── cli/                             # Command-line interface\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── run.rs                       # Run subcommand (start, status, history, tail)\n│   │   ├── project.rs\n│   │   ├── init.rs\n│   │   ├── config.rs\n│   │   ├── flow.rs\n│   │   ├── conformance.rs\n│   │   ├── daemon.rs\n│   │   └── requirements.rs\n│   ├── contexts/                        # Bounded contexts (DDD)\n│   │   ├── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── agent_execution/             # Backend invocation management\n│   │   │   ├── model.rs\n│   │   │   ├── service.rs\n│   │   │   └── session.rs\n│   │   ├── project_run_record/          # Core project/run state management\n│   │   │   ├── model.rs                 # Data models\n│   │   │   ├── service.rs               # Use case implementations\n│   │   │   ├── journal.rs               # Event journaling\n│   │   │   ├── queries.rs\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── workflow_composition/        # Stage orchestration\n│   │   │   ├── engine.rs                # Main execution engine\n│   │   │   ├── contracts.rs             # Stage contracts & validation\n│   │   │   ├── payloads.rs              # Typed payload models\n│   │   │   ├── renderers.rs             # Markdown artifact generation\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── workspace_governance/        # Workspace/project configuration\n│   │   │   ├── config.rs\n│   │   │   └── mod.rs\n│   │   ├── automation_runtime/\n│   │   ├── conformance_spec/\n│   │   └── requirements_drafting/\n│   └── shared/                          # Cross-cutting concerns\n│       ├── domain.rs                    # Domain value objects & enums\n│       ├── error.rs                     # Error types & handling\n│       └── mod.rs\n├── tests/unit/                          # Comprehensive test suite\n│   ├── workflow_engine_test.rs\n│   ├── project_run_record_test.rs\n│   └── [11 other test files]\n├── Cargo.toml\n└── Cargo.lock\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. Engine.rs (Workflow Composition Engine)\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs`\n\n**Purpose:** Core orchestration engine that executes the standard delivery flow from start to completion.\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n- **`standard_stage_plan(prompt_review_enabled: bool) -> Vec<StageId>`**\n  - Derives executable stage sequence from FlowPreset::Standard\n  - Optionally filters out PromptReview stage based on config\n  - Returns 8 stages with prompt_review=true, 7 without\n\n- **`role_for_stage(stage_id: StageId) -> BackendRole`**\n  - Maps each stage to a single deterministic backend role\n  - Delegates to `BackendRole::for_stage(stage_id)`\n\n- **`resolve_stage_plan(...) -> AppResult<Vec<StagePlan>>`**\n  - Resolves all stage targets ahead of execution\n  - Preflight validation structure with role, contract, and target per stage\n\n- **`preflight_check<A: AgentExecutionPort>(...) -> AppResult<()>`**\n  - Validates capability and availability for every stage target\n  - Fails fast before any state mutation\n\n- **`execute_standard_run<A, R, S>(...) -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Main state machine with 8-step progression:\n    1. Read current snapshot and validate preconditions\n    2. Derive stage plan with prompt_review config\n    3. Resolve backend targets for every stage\n    4. Preflight checks (all-or-nothing)\n    5. Generate run ID and read journal for sequence tracking\n    6. Persist run_started event + snapshot with Running status\n    7. Execute stages in canonical order (loop with error handling)\n    8. Mark run as Completed or Failed atomically\n  \n  - **Stage Execution Loop:**\n    - Emits `stage_entered` event\n    - Updates cursor in snapshot\n    - Logs to runtime logs\n    - Invokes backend with InvocationRequest (timeout, cancellation token, session policy)\n    - Evaluates contract: schema validation → semantic validation → rendering\n    - Persists payload + artifact pair atomically\n    - Emits `stage_completed` event\n    - Updates snapshot with next stage cursor\n    - On failure: calls `fail_run()`, returns error\n\n- **`fail_run(...) -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Records run failure with failure_class\n  - Persists `run_failed` event\n  - Updates snapshot to Failed status\n  - Returns AppError::RunStartFailed\n\n**Helper:**\n- **`generate_run_id() -> AppResult<RunId>`** - Timestamp-based run ID generation\n- **`project_root_path(base_dir, project_id) -> PathBuf`** - Standard path construction\n\n---\n\n### 2. Domain.rs (Shared Domain Model)\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs`\n\n**Key Enums & Stage-to-Role Mapping:**\n\n**BackendFamily** (4 variants):\n```\n- Claude       → \"opus-4.1\" (Planner default)\n- Codex        → \"gpt-5-codex\" (Implementer default)\n- OpenRouter   → \"openai/gpt-5\" (QaValidator default)\n- Stub         → \"stub-default\" (Testing)\n```\n\n**BackendRole** (5 variants):\n```\npub fn for_stage(stage_id: StageId) -> Self {\n    match stage_id {\n        PromptReview | Planning | DocsPlan | CiPlan => Planner,\n        Implementation | PlanAndImplement | ApplyFixes | DocsUpdate | CiUpdate => Implementer,\n        Qa | DocsValidation | CiValidation | AcceptanceQa => QaValidator,\n        Review | FinalReview => Reviewer,\n        CompletionPanel => CompletionJudge,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Default Targets by Role:**\n- Planner → Claude opus-4.1\n- Implementer → Codex gpt-5-codex\n- Reviewer → Claude sonnet-4.0\n- QaValidator → OpenRouter openai/gpt-5\n- CompletionJudge → Claude opus-4.1\n\n**StageId** (16 variants):\n- **Planning stages:** PromptReview, Planning, DocsPlan, CiPlan\n- **Execution stages:** Implementation, PlanAndImplement, ApplyFixes, DocsUpdate, CiUpdate\n- **Validation stages:** Qa, Review, CompletionPanel, AcceptanceQa, FinalReview, DocsValidation, CiValidation\n\n**FlowPreset** (4 variants):\n- Standard (8 stages: prompt_review → planning → implementation → qa → review → completion_panel → acceptance_qa → final_review)\n- QuickDev (4 stages: plan_and_implement → review → apply_fixes → final_review)\n- DocsChange (4 stages: docs_plan → docs_update → docs_validation → review)\n- CiImprovement (4 stages: ci_plan → ci_update → ci_validation → review)\n\n**StageCursor:**\n```rust\npub struct StageCursor {\n    pub stage: StageId,\n    pub cycle: u32,      // >= 1\n    pub attempt: u32,    // >= 1\n    pub completion_round: u32,  // >= 1\n}\n```\n- Encodes position within multi-cycle/attempt execution\n- Immutable once created; movements create new cursors\n\n**ProjectId & RunId:** Newtype wrappers with validation (non-empty, single path segment)\n\n**FailureClass:** (6 variants) TransportFailure, SchemaValidationFailure, DomainValidationFailure, Timeout, Cancellation, QaReviewOutcomeFailure\n\n**ResolvedBackendTarget:**\n```rust\npub struct ResolvedBackendTarget {\n    pub backend: BackendSpec,\n    pub model: ModelSpec,\n}\n```\n- Resolved configuration with capability checks\n- Supports session reuse, structured output, cancellation per backend\n\n---\n\n### 3. Project Run Record (State Management)\n\n#### Model (`model.rs`)\n\n**RunSnapshot** (canonical state in `run.json`):\n```rust\npub struct RunSnapshot {\n    pub active_run: Option<ActiveRun>,        // Current execution context\n    pub status: RunStatus,                    // NotStarted | Running | Paused | Completed | Failed\n    pub cycle_history: Vec<CycleHistoryEntry>,\n    pub completion_rounds: u32,\n    pub rollback_point_meta: RollbackPointMeta,\n    pub amendment_queue: AmendmentQueueState,\n    pub status_summary: String,               // Human-readable status\n}\n\npub struct ActiveRun {\n    pub run_id: String,\n    pub stage_cursor: StageCursor,\n    pub started_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n}\n```\n\n**Semantic Validation Rules:**\n- RunStatus::Running/Paused **requires** Some(active_run)\n- RunStatus::NotStarted **requires** None active_run\n- RunStatus::Completed/Failed **allows** either\n\n**JournalEvent** (stored in `journal.ndjson`, one per line):\n```rust\npub struct JournalEvent {\n    pub sequence: u64,                        // Monotonic, starts at 1\n    pub timestamp: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub event_type: JournalEventType,\n    pub details: serde_json::Value,\n}\n\npub enum JournalEventType {\n    ProjectCreated,      // Sequence 1\n    RunStarted,\n    StageEntered,\n    StageCompleted,      // Details: { run_id, stage_id, cycle, attempt, payload_id, artifact_id }\n    CycleAdvanced,\n    CompletionRoundAdvanced,\n    RunCompleted,\n    RunFailed,           // Details: { run_id, stage_id, failure_class, message }\n    RollbackCreated,\n    AmendmentQueued,\n}\n```\n\n**PayloadRecord** (stored in `history/payloads/{payload_id}.json`):\n```rust\npub struct PayloadRecord {\n    pub payload_id: String,                   // {run_id}-{stage_id}-c{cycle}-a{attempt}\n    pub stage_id: StageId,\n    pub cycle: u32,\n    pub attempt: u32,\n    pub created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub payload: serde_json::Value,           // Validated StagePayload as JSON\n}\n```\n\n**ArtifactRecord** (stored in `history/artifacts/{artifact_id}.json`):\n```rust\npub struct ArtifactRecord {\n    pub artifact_id: String,                  // {payload_id}-artifact\n    pub payload_id: String,\n    pub stage_id: StageId,\n    pub created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub content: String,                      // Markdown artifact\n}\n```\n\n**RuntimeLogEntry** (stored in `runtime/logs/run.ndjson`):\n```rust\npub struct RuntimeLogEntry {\n    pub timestamp: DateTime<Utc>,\n    pub level: LogLevel,                      // Debug | Info | Warn | Error\n    pub source: String,                       // e.g., \"engine\"\n    pub message: String,\n}\n```\n\n#### Service (`service.rs`)\n\n**Ports (traits for adapter implementation):**\n\n- **ProjectStorePort:** project_exists, read_project_record, list_project_ids, stage_delete, commit_delete, rollback_delete, create_project_atomic\n- **JournalStorePort:** read_journal, append_event\n- **ArtifactStorePort:** list_payloads, list_artifacts\n- **RuntimeLogStorePort:** read_runtime_logs\n- **RunSnapshotPort:** read_run_snapshot\n- **RunSnapshotWritePort:** write_run_snapshot (atomic)\n- **PayloadArtifactWritePort:** write_payload_artifact_pair (atomic pair)\n- **RuntimeLogWritePort:** append_runtime_log (best-effort)\n- **ActiveProjectPort:** read_active_project_id, clear_active_project, write_active_project\n\n**Use Cases:**\n\n- **`create_project(...) -> AppResult<ProjectRecord>`**\n  - Validates no duplicate project ID\n  - Creates record, initial snapshot, journal event\n  - Calls `store.create_project_atomic()` (all-or-nothing)\n\n- **`list_projects(...) -> AppResult<Vec<ProjectListEntry>>`**\n  - Reads all project IDs\n  - Enriches with active flag and metadata\n\n- **`show_project(...) -> AppResult<ProjectDetail>`**\n  - Reads record, snapshot, journal events\n  - Counts rollback points from journal\n  - Returns full detail view\n\n- **`delete_project(...) -> AppResult<()>`** (Transactional)\n  - Validates no active run\n  - Phase 1: stage_delete (project invisible but data remains)\n  - Phase 2: clear_active_project if was active (with rollback on failure)\n  - Phase 3: commit_delete (permanent removal, best-effort)\n\n- **`run_status(...) -> AppResult<RunStatusView>`**\n  - Queries current run status from snapshot\n  - Delegates to queries module\n\n- **`run_history(...) -> AppResult<RunHistoryView>`**\n  - Reads durable journal, payloads, artifacts\n  - Validates history consistency\n  - Returns structured history view\n\n- **`run_tail(...) -> AppResult<RunTailView>`**\n  - Durable history by default\n  - Optionally includes runtime logs\n  - Returns tail view for recent progress\n\n#### Journal (`journal.rs`)\n\n**Event Builders:**\n```rust\npub fn run_started_event(sequence, timestamp, run_id, first_stage) -> JournalEvent\npub fn stage_entered_event(sequence, timestamp, run_id, stage_id, cycle, attempt) -> JournalEvent\npub fn stage_completed_event(sequence, ..., payload_id, artifact_id) -> JournalEvent\npub fn run_completed_event(sequence, ..., completion_rounds) -> JournalEvent\npub fn run_failed_event(sequence, ..., stage_id, failure_class, message) -> JournalEvent\n```\n\n**Parsing & Validation:**\n- **`parse_journal(contents: &str) -> AppResult<Vec<JournalEvent>>`**\n  - Parses NDJSON line-by-line\n  - Validates monotonic sequence (first must be 1)\n  - Ensures first event is ProjectCreated\n  - Returns parsed, validated events in order\n\n- **`validate_sequence(last_sequence, event) -> AppResult<()>`**\n  - Enforces event.sequence == last_sequence + 1\n\n- **`last_sequence(events) -> u64`**\n  - Returns last sequence number or 0 if empty\n\n---\n\n### 4. Adapters/fs.rs (Filesystem Persistence)\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` (700 lines, 37 implementations)\n\n**Key Constants:**\n- WORKSPACE_DIR = \".ralph-burning\"\n- PROJECTS_DIR = \"projects\"\n- PROJECT_SUBDIRS = [\"history/payloads\", \"history/artifacts\", \"runtime/logs\", \"runtime/backend\", \"runtime/temp\", \"amendments\", \"rollback\"]\n\n**FileSystem (Static Utility Class):**\n\n- **`create_workspace(workspace_root, config, directories) -> AppResult<()>`**\n  - Creates workspace directory structure\n  - Writes workspace.toml atomically\n\n- **`write_atomic(path, contents) -> AppResult<()>`**\n  - Two-phase: write to temp file, fsync, atomic rename\n  - Timestamp-based temp naming to prevent collisions\n  - Cleans up temp file on failure\n\n- **`read_to_string(path) -> AppResult<String>`**\n- **`prompt_hash(contents) -> String`** - DefaultHasher-based hash\n- **`open_editor(path) -> AppResult<()>`** - Spawns EDITOR or VISUAL environment variable\n\n**Implementations (8 structs × 4-5 ports each):**\n\n1. **FsProjectStore** (ProjectStorePort)\n   - project_exists: checks project root + project.toml\n   - read_project_record: TOML deserialization\n   - list_project_ids: reads projects dir, skips hidden (staging/trash)\n   - stage_delete: atomic rename to `.{id}.pending-delete`\n   - commit_delete: removes pending-delete directory\n   - rollback_delete: renames pending-delete back to canonical path\n   - create_project_atomic: staging + atomic rename pattern\n\n2. **FsJournalStore** (JournalStorePort)\n   - read_journal: reads `journal.ndjson` and parses\n   - append_event: appends line with newline\n\n3. **FsArtifactStore** (ArtifactStorePort)\n   - list_payloads: reads `history/payloads/*.json`, sorts by created_at\n   - list_artifacts: reads `history/artifacts/*.json`, sorts by created_at\n\n4. **FsRuntimeLogStore** (RuntimeLogStorePort)\n   - read_runtime_logs: reads only newest `runtime/logs/*.ndjson` file\n\n5. **FsRunSnapshotStore** (RunSnapshotPort)\n   - read_run_snapshot: JSON deserialization + semantic validation\n\n6. **FsRunSnapshotWriteStore** (RunSnapshotWritePort)\n   - write_run_snapshot: pretty JSON via write_atomic\n\n7. **FsPayloadArtifactWriteStore** (PayloadArtifactWritePort)\n   - write_payload_artifact_pair: writes payload, then artifact (removes payload on artifact failure)\n\n8. **FsRuntimeLogWriteStore** (RuntimeLogWritePort)\n   - append_runtime_log: NDJSON append to `runtime/logs/run.ndjson`\n\n9. **FsActiveProjectStore** (ActiveProjectPort)\n   - read_active_project_id: reads `active-project` file\n   - clear_active_project: removes `active-project` file\n   - write_active_project: writes project ID via write_atomic\n\n10. **FsRawOutputStore** (RawOutputPort)\n    - persist_raw_output: writes to `runtime/backend/{invocation_id}.raw`\n\n11. **FsSessionStore** (SessionStorePort)\n    - load_sessions: reads `sessions.json`\n    - save_sessions: writes `sessions.json` atomically\n\n---\n\n### 5. Error.rs (Error Handling)\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs`\n\n**AppError Enum** (23 variants, all `#[error(...)]`):\n- AlreadyInitialized, WorkspaceConflict\n- InvalidStageCursorField, InvalidIdentifier, InvalidFlowPreset\n- UnsupportedWorkspaceVersion, UnknownConfigKey, InvalidConfigValue\n- NoActiveProject, ProjectNotFound, EditorFailed, DuplicateProject\n- CorruptRecord, InvalidPrompt, ActiveRunDelete\n- JournalSequence, RunStartFailed, UnsupportedFlow\n- PreflightFailed, StageCommitFailed, NotYetImplemented\n- BackendUnavailable, CapabilityMismatch, InvocationFailed, InvocationTimeout, InvocationCancelled\n- Io, TomlDeserialize, TomlSerialize, TomlEdit, SerdeJson\n\n**ContractError Enum** (4 variants):\n- SchemaValidation { stage_id, details }\n- DomainValidation { stage_id, details }\n- RenderError { stage_id, details }\n- QaReviewOutcome { stage_id, outcome }\n\n**Methods:**\n- `impl ContractError: failure_class() -> FailureClass, stage_id() -> StageId`\n- `impl AppError: failure_class() -> Option<FailureClass>`\n\n---\n\n### 6. CLI run.rs (Run Subcommand)\n\n**File:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs`\n\n**RunSubcommand Enum:**\n- Start - Execute standard run\n- Resume - Not yet implemented\n- Status - Report current run state\n- History - List durable journal events + payloads/artifacts\n- Tail { logs: bool } - Recent progress + optional runtime logs\n- Rollback { to: String, hard: bool } - Not yet implemented\n\n**Handlers:**\n\n- **`handle_start() -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Validate workspace version\n  - Resolve active project ID\n  - Read project record\n  - Enforce FlowPreset::Standard only\n  - Read run snapshot\n  - Validate preconditions (status == NotStarted, no active run)\n  - Load effective config\n  - Call engine::execute_standard_run with all port implementations\n  - Print completion message\n\n- **`handle_status() -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Load workspace config\n  - Resolve active project\n  - Call service::run_status\n  - Print status summary\n\n- **`handle_history() -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Resolve active project\n  - Call service::run_history\n  - Print journal events, payloads, artifacts\n\n- **`handle_tail(include_logs: bool) -> AppResult<()>` (async)**\n  - Resolve active project\n  - Call service::run_tail\n  - Print durable history + optional runtime logs\n\n- **`build_agent_execution_service() -> AgentExecutionService<StubBackendAdapter, FsRawOutputStore, FsSessionStore>`**\n  - Default service builder using stub backend for testing\n\n---\n\n### 7. Test Files\n\n#### workflow_engine_test.rs (389 lines)\n\n**Stage Plan Tests:**\n- `stage_plan_with_prompt_review_enabled()` - Asserts 8 stages\n- `stage_plan_with_prompt_review_disabled()` - Asserts 7 stages, no PromptReview\n- `role_mapping_is_deterministic()` - Validates all 8 stage-to-role mappings\n\n**Happy Path Tests:**\n- `happy_path_standard_run_completes()` - Full end-to-end execution\n  - Asserts status == Completed, active_run is None\n  - Verifies >= 19 journal events (project_created + run_started + 16 stage events + run_completed)\n  - Confirms 8 payloads, 8 artifacts written\n\n- `happy_path_prompt_review_disabled()` - Standard run without prompt_review\n  - Asserts 7 payloads, no prompt_review stage_entered events\n\n**Precondition Failure Tests:**\n- `run_start_rejects_already_running()` - Fails if status != NotStarted\n- `run_start_rejects_completed_project()` - Fails if status == Completed\n\n**Preflight Failure Tests:**\n- `preflight_failure_leaves_state_unchanged()` - Uses unavailable backend\n  - Verifies snapshot still NotStarted\n  - Verifies journal only has project_created\n  - Verifies no payloads/artifacts created\n\n**Plan Resolution Tests:**\n- `resolve_stage_plan_produces_correct_targets()` - 8 stages resolved correctly\n- `preflight_check_succeeds_with_default_stub()` - Default adapter passes\n- `preflight_check_fails_with_unavailable_backend()` - Fails as expected\n\n#### project_run_record_test.rs (840 lines)\n\n**Domain Tests:**\n- `run_snapshot_initial_has_no_active_run()` - Initial state validation\n- `session_store_empty_has_no_sessions()` - Empty store\n- `project_record_flow_is_immutable_after_creation()` - Immutability\n- `journal_event_types_serialize_to_snake_case()` - Serde format\n\n**Service Tests with Fake Ports:**\n- `create_project_succeeds_with_valid_input()` - Success path\n- `create_project_fails_on_duplicate_id()` - Duplicate rejection\n- `list_projects_returns_entries_with_active_flag()` - List with active marking\n- `list_projects_with_no_active_project()` - No active case\n- `show_project_returns_detail()` - Detail view\n- `show_project_fails_for_missing_project()` - Missing project error\n- `delete_project_succeeds_when_no_active_run()` - Deletion success\n- `delete_project_fails_with_active_run()` - Active run blocks deletion\n- `delete_project_fails_for_missing_project()` - Missing project error\n- `run_status_reports_not_started_when_no_active_run()` - Status reporting\n- `run_status_reports_running_with_stage_cursor()` - Running status with cursor\n\n**Semantic Validation Tests:**\n- `run_snapshot_validates_running_without_active_run_as_corrupt()` - Corruption detection\n- `run_snapshot_validates_paused_without_active_run_as_corrupt()`\n- `run_snapshot_validates_not_started_with_active_run_as_corrupt()`\n- `run_snapshot_validates_completed_without_active_run_as_valid()` - Valid terminal state\n- `run_snapshot_validates_failed_without_active_run_as_valid()`\n\n**Transactional Delete Tests:**\n- `delete_project_does_not_touch_pointer_on_stage_failure()` - Rollback on stage failure\n- `delete_project_rolls_back_on_clear_pointer_failure()` - Rollback on clear failure\n- `delete_project_succeeds_for_completed_terminal_state()` - Terminal state deletion\n\n**Model Serialization Tests:**\n- `failed_stage_summary_serializes_correctly()` - JSON roundtrip\n- `run_status_display_matches_display_str()` - Display trait\n- `run_snapshot_completed_has_no_active_run()` - Terminal state invariants\n- `run_snapshot_failed_has_no_active_run()`\n\n---\n\n### Key Architectural Patterns\n\n1. **Port & Adapter Pattern:** All persistence operations are abstract through traits (ports) with concrete filesystem implementations (adapters)\n\n2. **Bounded Contexts:** Clear separation:\n   - workflow_composition (orchestration)\n   - project_run_record (state management)\n   - agent_execution (backend interaction)\n   - workspace_governance (configuration)\n\n3. **Transactional Operations:**\n   - Atomic file writes with temp file + rename pattern\n   - Staging directory for project creation\n   - Multi-phase delete with rollback semantics\n\n4. **Deterministic Flow:**\n   - Stage → Role mapping is fixed in BackendRole::for_stage\n   - Flow definitions are constants\n   - Journal sequence is monotonic and validated\n\n5. **Contract-Driven Validation:**\n   - Three payload families (Planning, Execution, Validation)\n   - Schema → Semantic → Outcome → Rendering pipeline\n   - Each stage maps to exactly one contract\n\n6. **Error Classification:**\n   - FailureClass enums for retry/terminal policy decisions\n   - ContractError maps to FailureClass deterministically\n   - AppError has optional failure_class for context\n\n---\n\n### File Paths Summary\n\n**Critical Files:**\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs` - Main orchestration\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/domain.rs` - Domain model & stage-to-role mapping\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/model.rs` - State models\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/service.rs` - Use cases\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/contexts/project_run_record/journal.rs` - Event journaling\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/adapters/fs.rs` - Filesystem layer (37 implementations)\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/shared/error.rs` - Error handling\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/src/cli/run.rs` - CLI run subcommand\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/workflow_engine_test.rs` - Engine tests\n- `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/unit/project_run_record_test.rs` - State management tests\n\n**Total Source Files:** 37 Rust files across contexts, adapters, CLI, and shared modules"}],"totalDurationMs":96809,"totalTokens":91717,"totalToolUseCount":27,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1460,"cache_read_input_tokens":82759,"output_tokens":7496,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1460},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
